00:34:25,462 --> 00:34:27,362
噢，不完全是
{\fscx80\fscy80}Well, it wasn't exactly that.{\r}

372
00:34:27,464 --> 00:34:31,525
我来找你是想说件事的 但我见到你后，却完了
{\fscx80\fscy80}I came here to talk to you about something, but after I saw you, it slipped my mind.{\r}

373
00:34:31,601 --> 00:34:34,092
-那应该不是很重要 -我想你是对的
{\fscx80\fscy80}It couldn't have been very important then. Guess you're right.{\r}

374
00:34:35,605 --> 00:34:37,573
或许你坐在阳台里？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Why don't you sit down on the porch?{\r}

375
00:34:37,674 --> 00:34:40,006
我拿点柠檬水给 或许你会回忆起的
{\fscx80\fscy80}I'll get you a lemonade and maybe you'll think of it.{\r}

376
00:34:40,077 --> 00:34:42,409
你不但漂亮而且周到
{\fscx80\fscy80}You're not only beautiful, you're considerate too.{\r}

377
00:34:44,414 --> 00:34:46,814
-安尼卡！ -你好，马洛先生！
{\fscx80\fscy80}Arnie! Hello, Mr. Marlow!{\r}

378
00:34:46,883 --> 00:34:48,817
你好.你拿着什么？ 一只野兔？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Hi. What do you got? A rabbit?{\r}

379
00:34:48,885 --> 00:34:52,013
死的.你拿着什么？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Dead. What have you got?{\r}

380
00:34:52,089 --> 00:34:57,322
噢，我拿着一只青蛙
{\fscx80\fscy80}Oh, I got me a little frog. [Yells]{\r}

381
00:34:57,394 --> 00:35:00,522
-这里 -它饿了，要找妈妈
{\fscx80\fscy80}There he is. It's hungry. It needs a mother.{\r}

382
00:35:05,902 --> 00:35:08,996
我和你交换
{\fscx80\fscy80}- [Mrs. Rogers, Giggling ] - I'll trade ya.{\r}

383
00:35:09,106 --> 00:35:12,166
-你想当青蛙的妈妈？ -用野兔换青蛙
{\fscx80\fscy80}Your mother for mine? The rabbit for the frog.{\r}

384
00:35:12,242 --> 00:35:17,771
-给你，安尼卡 -我想你做一笔好买卖
{\fscx80\fscy80}It's yours, Arnie. I think you got the best deal.{\r}

385
00:35:17,848 --> 00:35:19,816
死野兔不用吃东西的
{\fscx80\fscy80}Dead rabbits don't eat.{\r}

386
00:35:19,850 --> 00:35:23,411
好的 我拿回厨房给它喝点柠檬水
{\fscx80\fscy80}Well, I'll just take it in the kitchen and give him some lemonade.{\r}

387
00:35:31,128 --> 00:35:34,825
四脚的野兔，它被杀死了
{\fscx80\fscy80}Four rabbit's feet, and he got killed.{\r}

388
00:35:34,931 --> 00:35:39,163
-他该盖上些树叶 -戴上马蹄
{\fscx80\fscy80}He should've carried a four-leaf clover too. And a horseshoe.{\r}

389
00:35:39,236 --> 00:35:42,034
兔子是如何生出来的？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Say, how do rabbits get to be born?{\r}

390
00:35:43,140 --> 00:35:46,041
-和大象一样 -噢，那当然
{\fscx80\fscy80}Same way elephants do. Oh, sure.{\r}

391
00:35:46,143 --> 00:35:48,771
怎么以前没见你来过我家？
{\fscx80\fscy80}How come you never came over to visit me before?{\r}

392
00:35:48,845 --> 00:35:50,779
我以前不知道你有个 怎么美丽的妈妈啊，安尼卡
{\fscx80\fscy80}Didn't know you had such a pretty mother, Arnie.{\r}

393
00:35:50,847 --> 00:35:54,874
如果你认为她漂亮 你也该看看我的弹弓
{\fscx80\fscy80}If you think she's pretty, you should see my slingshot.{\r}

394
00:35:54,951 --> 00:35:59,217
-噢，或许我明天来 -什么时候呢？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Hmm, perhaps I'll come back tomorrow. When's that?{\r}

395
00:35:59,289 --> 00:36:02,884
-明天 -那是昨天 今天是明天
{\fscx80\fscy80}The day after today. That's yesterday. Today's tomorrow.{\r}

396
00:36:02,959 --> 00:36:07,623
-是啊-昨天什么时候是明天啊？ 马洛先生
{\fscx80\fscy80}It was. When was tomorrow yesterday, Mr. Marlow?{\r}

397
00:36:08,999 --> 00:36:11,968
-今天 -噢，当然.昨天
{\fscx80\fscy80}Today. Oh, sure. Yesterday.{\r}

398
00:36:12,002 --> 00:36:14,903
你永远都搞不懂安尼卡的 他有自己的时间
{\fscx80\fscy80}You'll never make sense out of Arnie. He's got his own timing.{\r}

399
00:36:20,377 --> 00:36:22,436
谢谢
{\fscx80\fscy80}Thank you.{\r}

400
00:36:22,512 --> 00:36:25,106
-柠檬水，安尼卡？ -我已经偷喝了两杯
{\fscx80\fscy80}Lemonade, Arnie? I already swiped two glasses.{\r}

401
00:36:25,182 --> 00:36:29,585
-是我已经给了你两杯 -偷更有趣
{\fscx80\fscy80}I would've given you two glasses. It's more fun swiped.{\r}

402
00:36:29,619 --> 00:36:32,315
-我能借你的兔子吗？马洛先生 -当然，安尼卡
{\fscx80\fscy80}Can I borrow your rabbit, Mr. Marlow? Sure, Arnie.{\r}

403
00:36:32,389 --> 00:36:34,323
你打算怎样处置它啊？
{\fscx80\fscy80}What are you gonna do with it?{\r}

404
00:36:34,391 --> 00:36:37,019
你永远不知道一只死的野兔 什么时候会派上用场的
{\fscx80\fscy80}You never know when a dead rabbit might come in handy.{\r}

405
00:36:39,196 --> 00:36:42,427
它已经为我拿到了一只青蛙
{\fscx80\fscy80}It already got me one frog.{\r}

406
00:36:46,403 --> 00:36:51,306
-安尼卡，你现在要去哪儿啊？ -去做一些买卖
{\fscx80\fscy80}Arnie! Where are you going now? To make some more trades!{\r}

407
00:36:51,408 --> 00:36:54,605
-安尼卡，准时回来吃午饭啊 -我尽量
{\fscx80\fscy80}Arnie, come home in time for supper. I'll try.{\r}

408
00:36:54,711 --> 00:36:57,202
你姓什么？
{\fscx80\fscy80}[Horn Honking ] What's your given name?{\r}

409
00:36:57,314 --> 00:37:02,911
-如果你不想回答，就捏造一个吧 -詹尼弗，詹尼弗.罗杰斯
{\fscx80\fscy80}If you don't want to tell me, just make one up. Jennifer. Jennifer Rogers.{\r}

410
00:37:03,019 --> 00:37:08,719
听好听的 呃，那个在山上的人是谁？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Nice. Um, who's the man up on the path?{\r}

411
00:37:08,758 --> 00:37:11,989
-什么人？ -就是，哈里.那个死人
{\fscx80\fscy80}What man? You know, Harry, the dead man.{\r}

412
00:37:12,062 --> 00:37:17,056
噢，他啊.他是我的丈夫
{\fscx80\fscy80}Oh, him. That's my husband.{\r}

413
00:37:17,134 --> 00:37:19,068
那么你的丈夫是死了？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Your husband's dead then?{\r}

414
00:37:22,439 --> 00:37:24,771
-你的柠檬水够甜吗？   -
{\fscx80\fscy80}Is your lemonade sweet enough? Seems to be.{\r}

415
00:37:24,841 --> 00:37:29,540
-我喜欢酸点 -哈里是安尼卡的父亲了？
{\fscx80\fscy80}I like it tart. Harry is Arnie's father then?{\r}

416
00:37:30,680 --> 00:37:32,875
不，安尼卡的父亲已经死了 -哈里也死了
{\fscx80\fscy80}No, Arnie's father's dead. So is Harry.{\r}

417
00:37:34,784 --> 00:37:37,685
谢天谢地 他可能好得活不成了
{\fscx80\fscy80}Thank goodness. He was too good to live.{\r}

418
00:37:37,754 --> 00:37:40,587
从他的相貌来看 他似乎不是太友善那种
{\fscx80\fscy80}From his looks, he didn't appear to me to be the kind who was too good.{\r}

419
00:37:40,657 --> 00:37:43,182
噢，他是挺友善的.非常的好
{\fscx80\fscy80}Well, he was. Horribly good.{\r}

420
00:37:43,260 --> 00:37:47,754
我也喜欢你的嘴巴 特别当你所“好”的时候
{\fscx80\fscy80}I like your mouth too, especially when you say good.{\r}

421
00:37:50,967 --> 00:37:54,733
-你要来多杯柠檬水吗？ -等会儿吧，谢谢
{\fscx80\fscy80}Will you have some more lemonade? Maybe later. Thanks.{\r}

422
00:37:54,804 --> 00:37:56,772
安尼卡是在哪儿得到这野兔的？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Where'd Arnie get the rabbit?{\r}

423
00:37:58,275 --> 00:38:01,711
他找到的 我想是怀尔斯船长射中的
{\fscx80\fscy80}He found it. I think Capt. Wiles shot it.{\r}

424
00:38:01,878 --> 00:38:05,871
如果你不介意的话 我想听听关于你生活的故事
{\fscx80\fscy80}I'd like to hear more of your life story, if you don't mind.{\r}

425
00:38:05,982 --> 00:38:07,882
我们对哈里都所知甚少
{\fscx80\fscy80}You see, we don't know quite what to do with Harry.{\r}

426
00:38:07,984 --> 00:38:10,111
或许你能给点头绪
{\fscx80\fscy80}Thought you might have some suggestions.{\r}

427
00:38:10,187 --> 00:38:12,553
你说他的一切都与我无关
{\fscx80\fscy80}Hmm. You can stuff him for all I care.{\r}

428
00:38:12,622 --> 00:38:15,648
说饱他就把他丢进一个玻璃瓶
{\fscx80\fscy80}Stuff him and put him in a glass case,{\r}

429
00:38:15,725 --> 00:38:18,592
而我唯一的建议 是冷却的玻璃瓶
{\fscx80\fscy80}only I'd suggest frosted glass.{\r}

430
00:38:20,297 --> 00:38:23,198
除了娶了你 他还对你干了什么？
{\fscx80\fscy80}What did he do to you, besides marry you?{\r}

431
00:38:25,502 --> 00:38:29,905
听着，我多次向别人说起哈里
{\fscx80\fscy80}Look, I've wanted to explain about Harry a lot of times,{\r}

432
00:38:30,006 --> 00:38:35,239
但没人能明白 而最不能明白的是哈里
{\fscx80\fscy80}[Church Bells Ringing ] But nobody would understand, least of all Harry.{\r}

433
00:38:36,913 --> 00:38:41,816
但你，你有艺术家的头脑 或许你能看透
{\fscx80\fscy80}But you... You've got an artistic mind. You can see the finer things.{\r}

434
00:38:41,918 --> 00:38:44,944
我可挺幸运的 继续，告诉我所以一切
{\fscx80\fscy80}When I'm lucky. Go on. Tell me everything.{\r}

435
00:38:45,021 --> 00:38:48,616
都说出来吧
{\fscx80\fscy80}Let it all out.{\r}

436
00:38:48,725 --> 00:38:52,217
很久以前，我在恋爱中
{\fscx80\fscy80}It was a long time ago and I was in love.{\r}

437
00:38:52,329 --> 00:38:54,820
-我很投入 -他叫什么名字？
{\fscx80\fscy80}I was too much in love. What was his name?{\r}

438
00:38:54,931 --> 00:38:56,831
罗伯特
{\fscx80\fscy80}Robert.{\r}

439
00:38:56,933 --> 00:38:59,925
我们都同意忽视对方的家人 和其它一切然后就结婚
{\fscx80\fscy80}We'd agreed to overlook each other's families and everything and get married.{\r}

440
00:39:00,036 --> 00:39:01,936
-是吗？   -噢，对
{\fscx80\fscy80}Did you? Oh, yes.{\r}

441
00:39:04,241 --> 00:39:08,041
-然后罗伯特就被杀了 -噢？
{\fscx80\fscy80}And then Robert got killed. Oh?{\r}

442
00:39:08,078 --> 00:39:12,139
我伤心了六周
{\fscx80\fscy80}I was heartbroken for six weeks.{\r}

443
00:39:12,249 --> 00:39:15,184
然后我发现怀了安尼卡
{\fscx80\fscy80}Then I discovered little Arnie was on the way.{\r}

444
00:39:15,252 --> 00:39:18,653
-真让人惊讶 -这时哈里就出现了
{\fscx80\fscy80}Must have been a shock. Well, that's where Harry came in.{\r}

445
00:39:18,755 --> 00:39:23,385
哈里是个英俊的英雄 哈里是个圣人
{\fscx80\fscy80}Harry the handsome hero. Harry the saint.{\r}

446
00:39:23,460 --> 00:39:26,361
-哈里是最好的 -我没听清他的姓
{\fscx80\fscy80}Harry the good. I didn't catch his last name.{\r}

447
00:39:26,463 --> 00:39:29,364
哈里.沃普，罗伯特的哥哥
{\fscx80\fscy80}Harry Worp, Robert's brother... his older brother.{\r}

448
00:39:29,466 --> 00:39:31,366
他爱上你了？
{\fscx80\fscy80}And he fell in love with you?{\r}

449
00:39:31,468 --> 00:39:34,437
如果他爱上我了 我就不会这么烦了
{\fscx80\fscy80}If he'd have fallen in love with me, I wouldn't have minded.{\r}

450
00:39:34,504 --> 00:39:38,031
他想娶我，因为他是 罗伯特的哥哥而且有种优越感
{\fscx80\fscy80}He wanted to marry me because he was Robert's brother and felt noble.{\r}

451
00:39:38,108 --> 00:39:40,633
而你以为他爱上你了？
{\fscx80\fscy80}But you thought he was in love with you?{\r}

452
00:39:40,710 --> 00:39:44,578
因为有了安尼卡 所以我决定让他爱我
{\fscx80\fscy80}And I decided to let him love me because of Arnie.{\r}

453
00:39:44,614 --> 00:39:47,276
就在我结婚的第二天晚上 我知道了真相
{\fscx80\fscy80}It was on my second wedding night that I learned the truth.{\r}

454
00:39:49,286 --> 00:39:51,948
第一天你不知道？
{\fscx80\fscy80}You didn't learn on your first?{\r}

455
00:39:52,022 --> 00:39:57,289
那是个可怕的真相…
{\fscx80\fscy80}[ Dog Barking ] This was a terrible truth...{\r}

456
00:39:57,394 --> 00:40:00,727
-关于哈里的真相 -发生了什么？
{\fscx80\fscy80}the truth about Harry. Just what happened?{\r}

457
00:40:02,632 --> 00:40:06,124
-你有多大了，马洛先生？ -大概30岁
{\fscx80\fscy80}- How old are you, Mr. Marlow? - About thirty.{\r}

458
00:40:09,606 --> 00:40:13,167
是这样的
{\fscx80\fscy80}This is what happened.{\r}

459
00:40:13,243 --> 00:40:18,010
我自己在酒店里 我穿上最好的睡衣
{\fscx80\fscy80}I was in the hotel room alone. I put on my best nightie.{\r}

460
00:40:18,114 --> 00:40:20,548
-你明白吗？ -完全明白
{\fscx80\fscy80}- You understand? - Perfectly.{\r}

461
00:40:22,419 --> 00:40:24,444
尽管我对哈里没有什么感觉
{\fscx80\fscy80}Although I had no true feeling for Harry,{\r}

462
00:40:24,521 --> 00:40:28,719
但我还是让自己兴奋起来 因为我认为他爱我
{\fscx80\fscy80}I had worked myself into a certain enthusiasm because I thought he loved me.{\r}

463
00:40:28,825 --> 00:40:30,725
可不容易啊
{\fscx80\fscy80}Must have been hard work.{\r}

464
00:40:32,128 --> 00:40:34,892
那晚满月，我坐在窗边
{\fscx80\fscy80}There was a full moon, and I sat by the window...{\r}

465
00:40:34,964 --> 00:40:37,990
因为我觉得这样更能 展现我的新睡衣
{\fscx80\fscy80}because I thought it would show off my new nightie to advantage.{\r}

466
00:40:38,068 --> 00:40:43,734
-很自然 -我不知道我为何要和你说这个
{\fscx80\fscy80}- Naturally. - I don't know why I'm telling you all this.{\r}

467
00:40:43,840 --> 00:40:46,172
你可是个外人 我没让你觉得闷吧？
{\fscx80\fscy80}You a perfect stranger too. I'm not boring you, am I?{\r}

468
00:40:47,644 --> 00:40:49,578
没有，一点也不
{\fscx80\fscy80}No. No. Not at all.{\r}

469
00:40:51,348 --> 00:40:54,374
-来到柠檬水怎样？ -不用了
{\fscx80\fscy80}How about some more lemonade? Uh, soon. Soon.{\r}

470
00:40:56,286 --> 00:41:00,245
-我说到哪儿了？ -你坐在窗边因为那晚是满月
{\fscx80\fscy80}Oh, where was I? You were sitting by the window because there was a full moon,{\r}

471
00:41:00,357 --> 00:41:02,917
你让自己兴奋起来
{\fscx80\fscy80}and you'd worked yourself up to a certain enthusiasm.{\r}

472
00:41:02,992 --> 00:41:06,257
我都说了这个？
{\fscx80\fscy80}I said all that?{\r}

473
00:41:06,363 --> 00:41:09,491
嗯，哈里是什么时候进来的？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Uh, when does Harry come in?{\r}

474
00:41:09,566 --> 00:41:12,467
他没进来，他永远也没进来
{\fscx80\fscy80}He doesn't. He never came in.{\r}

475
00:41:12,569 --> 00:41:16,699
-他第二天打来电话 -第二天？
{\fscx80\fscy80}He called the following morning. The following morning?{\r}

476
00:41:16,773 --> 00:41:19,867
就在那天晚上 他在酒店的走廊里买了本杂志
{\fscx80\fscy80}In the hotel lobby the night before, he had bought a magazine.{\r}

477
00:41:19,976 --> 00:41:22,035
-里面有他的星座 -不好吗？
{\fscx80\fscy80}- His horoscope was in it. - Bad?{\r}

478
00:41:22,112 --> 00:41:25,411
写着，他是金牛座
{\fscx80\fscy80}It said... He was a Taurus.{\r}

479
00:41:25,482 --> 00:41:28,474
写着 “那天千万别开展什么新项目”
{\fscx80\fscy80}It said, "Don't start any new project that day.{\r}

480
00:41:28,585 --> 00:41:30,917
“不会有好结果的”
{\fscx80\fscy80}It could never be finished."{\r}

481
00:41:30,987 --> 00:41:35,253
-你怎么办？ -我离开了他，回到了我妈妈的家
{\fscx80\fscy80}And what did you do? I left him on the spot, and went home to Mother's.{\r}

482
00:41:35,325 --> 00:41:39,523
-结束 -真是让人心酸的故事
{\fscx80\fscy80}- The end. - What a poignant story.{\r}

483
00:41:39,596 --> 00:41:44,124
-我知道你明白了，没人会明白的 -你母亲也不明白吗？
{\fscx80\fscy80}I knew you'd understand. Nobody else does. Not even Mother?{\r}

484
00:41:44,200 --> 00:41:47,033
噢，她以为我会回到他身边 但我没有
{\fscx80\fscy80}Well, she thought I should live with him, but I wouldn't.{\r}

485
00:41:47,103 --> 00:41:50,664
他来过让我回去 但都被我拒绝了
{\fscx80\fscy80}He pestered me to go back, but I always refused.{\r}

486
00:41:50,740 --> 00:41:54,198
噢，想想 某天晚上我要他干什么…
{\fscx80\fscy80}Well, suppose some night I wanted him to do something...{\r}

487
00:41:54,310 --> 00:41:56,938
例如洗碗
{\fscx80\fscy80}like the dishes, for example.{\r}

488
00:41:57,013 --> 00:41:59,072
而他的星座劝他别干
{\fscx80\fscy80}His horoscope just wouldn't let him.{\r}

489
00:41:59,149 --> 00:42:04,018
-你做得很对 -有些事我是不想自己干的
{\fscx80\fscy80}You're absolutely right. There are some things I just don't like to do by myself.{\r}

490
00:42:04,053 --> 00:42:07,648
如果真正理解你就不会责怪你
{\fscx80\fscy80}And no one with any true understanding would blame you for it.{\r}

491
00:42:09,626 --> 00:42:13,653
安尼卡出生后，我就搬到了 我认为哈里找不到我的地方去了
{\fscx80\fscy80}As soon as Arnie was born, I moved away to where I thought Harry could never find me.{\r}

492
00:42:13,730 --> 00:42:16,324
我改了名字和…
{\fscx80\fscy80}I changed my name and...{\r}

493
00:42:16,433 --> 00:42:19,334
但他还不死心？
{\fscx80\fscy80}But he was persistent?{\r}

494
00:42:19,436 --> 00:42:21,836
今天早上有人敲我的门
{\fscx80\fscy80}This morning there was a knock on the door.{\r}

495
00:42:21,871 --> 00:42:24,669
我开门前就知道是他
{\fscx80\fscy80}Before I opened it, I knew he was standing on the other side.{\r}

496
00:42:24,741 --> 00:42:30,202
-他来要什么？ -我！他来要我，因为我是他的妻
{\fscx80\fscy80}What did he want? Me! He wanted me because I was his wife.{\r}

497
00:42:30,280 --> 00:42:34,239
他需要我，因为 正如他所说的，他有鼓冲动
{\fscx80\fscy80}He wanted me because, as he put it, he suddenly felt some basic urge{\r}

498
00:42:34,284 --> 00:42:36,275
-寂寞   -你呢？
{\fscx80\fscy80}loneliness. What'd you feel?{\r}

499
00:42:36,352 --> 00:42:40,618
我觉得很恶心 你看到他的胡子和波浪发型吗？
{\fscx80\fscy80}I felt sick. Did you see his mustache and his wavy hair?{\r}

500
00:42:40,690 --> 00:42:42,658
有，但我看到他时 他已经死了
{\fscx80\fscy80}Yeah, but when I saw him, he was dead.{\r}

501
00:42:42,692 --> 00:42:46,321
对，和他活着时是一样的 活着时只不过是站在罢了
{\fscx80\fscy80}Yeah, he looked exactly the same when he was alive, except he was vertical.{\r}

502
00:42:46,396 --> 00:42:49,422
-他进了屋子吧，他说了什么？
{\fscx80\fscy80}So he entered. What'd you say? Nothing.{\r}

503
00:42:49,499 --> 00:42:52,024
我用奶瓶敲他的头，敲到傻了
{\fscx80\fscy80}I hit him over the head with a milk bottle and knocked him silly.{\r}

504
00:42:52,101 --> 00:42:56,834
-傻了？ -神经不正常啊
{\fscx80\fscy80}- Silly? - Bats. Tappy.{\r}

505
00:42:56,906 --> 00:43:00,034
他摇摇晃晃地走向森林 不停地说他要找他妻子…
{\fscx80\fscy80}He went staggering up towards the woods saying he was gonna find his wife...{\r}

506
00:43:00,109 --> 00:43:01,974
如果这没要他命就带她回家
{\fscx80\fscy80}and drag her home if it killed him.{\r}

507
00:43:02,078 --> 00:43:04,171
显然要了他的命
{\fscx80\fscy80}Apparently it did.{\r}

508
00:43:07,083 --> 00:43:10,246
来多杯柠檬水吧
{\fscx80\fscy80}[Horn Honking ] Have some more lemonade.{\r}

509
00:43:51,661 --> 00:43:55,188
噢，怀尔斯船长 真让人意外啊！
{\fscx80\fscy80}Why, Capt. Wiles. What a surprise.{\r}

510
00:43:55,265 --> 00:43:57,733
可这是你邀请我来的 格勒夫利小姐
{\fscx80\fscy80}But you invited me, Miss Gravely.{\r}

511
00:43:57,767 --> 00:44:00,634
-起码我记得是这样的 -当然了，船长
{\fscx80\fscy80}At least that's how I remember it. Of course I did, Captain.{\r}

512
00:44:00,737 --> 00:44:03,638
但还有有点意外
{\fscx80\fscy80}But somehow, it's still a surprise.{\r}

513
00:44:03,740 --> 00:44:07,574
噢，对.你真了解男人的需要
{\fscx80\fscy80}Oh, yes. You certainly know how to make a man feel wanted.{\r}

514
00:44:07,644 --> 00:44:09,669
进屋吧，船长
{\fscx80\fscy80}Won't you come in, Captain?{\r}

515
00:44:09,746 --> 00:44:13,705
噢，谢谢.很荣幸
{\fscx80\fscy80}Oh, thank you. I've-I've looked forward to it.{\r}

516
00:44:29,766 --> 00:44:32,826
尝到了真正厨师 做蓝莓松饼的手艺了
{\fscx80\fscy80}Takes a real cook to make a good blueberry muffin...{\r}

517
00:44:32,902 --> 00:44:34,870
蓝莓味非常浓郁
{\fscx80\fscy80}to keep the blueberries from sitting on the bottom.{\r}

518
00:44:34,904 --> 00:44:38,362
高山矮树丛蓝莓 这就是奥妙所在
{\fscx80\fscy80}High-bush blueberries. That's the secret.{\r}

519
00:44:38,408 --> 00:44:43,539
我就在你射杀那个 不幸的人的附近采集的
{\fscx80\fscy80}I picked 'em up near where you shot that unfortunate man.{\r}

520
00:44:48,685 --> 00:44:51,279
这个杯子真漂亮
{\fscx80\fscy80}A real handsome man's cup.{\r}

521
00:44:52,388 --> 00:44:54,948
我们家用了很多年了
{\fscx80\fscy80}It's been in the family for years.{\r}

522
00:44:55,024 --> 00:44:57,822
我的父亲一直都用它 直到他去世
{\fscx80\fscy80}My father always used it up until he died.{\r}

523
00:45:01,698 --> 00:45:04,792
我相信他死得很平静 在睡梦中死去
{\fscx80\fscy80}I trust he died peacefully... slipped away in the night.{\r}

524
00:45:04,901 --> 00:45:07,802
他是被脱粒机弄死的
{\fscx80\fscy80}He was caught in a threshing machine.{\r}

525
00:45:10,538 --> 00:45:13,735
-希望我没掉你胃口，船长 -噢，没有.格勒夫利小姐
{\fscx80\fscy80}Hope I haven't distressed you, Captain. Oh, not at all, Miss Gravely.{\r}

526
00:45:13,808 --> 00:45:17,835
没关系 我总是看到事物阴暗的一面
{\fscx80\fscy80}Not at all. I'm used to looking on the rough side of things.{\r}

527
00:45:17,912 --> 00:45:20,142
我面对死亡的次数很多了
{\fscx80\fscy80}I am man who's faced death many times.{\r}

528
00:45:21,249 --> 00:45:24,707
-最近也是吧   -对
{\fscx80\fscy80}- Rather recently too. - Yeah.{\r}

529
00:45:29,757 --> 00:45:33,386
-安尼卡，你拿什么来这儿？ -一只野兔
{\fscx80\fscy80}- Arnie. What are you carrying there? - A rabbit.{\r}

530
00:45:33,461 --> 00:45:35,656
一只野兔？
{\fscx80\fscy80}[Captain ] A rabbit?{\r}

531
00:45:37,532 --> 00:45:40,729
-你说这是什么？ -死兔.不是我的
{\fscx80\fscy80}- What do you call it? - Dead. It ain't mine.{\r}

532
00:45:40,835 --> 00:45:44,327
-是谁的？ -你的，你弄枪射死的
{\fscx80\fscy80}Well, whose is it? Yours. You shot it with your gun.{\r}

533
00:45:44,439 --> 00:45:46,430
肯定是你今天杀的
{\fscx80\fscy80}You must've killed it today.{\r}

534
00:45:46,541 --> 00:45:48,634
-拿来焖可不错啊 一只野兔！
{\fscx80\fscy80}- It should make a nice stew for ya. - A rabbit!{\r}

535
00:45:48,743 --> 00:45:51,576
我还是杀了只兔子！ 你在哪儿找到的？
{\fscx80\fscy80}I finally killed a rabbit! Where did you find it?{\r}

536
00:45:51,646 --> 00:45:53,580
在蓝莓松饼里
{\fscx80\fscy80}In the blueberry muffins.{\r}

537
00:45:53,648 --> 00:45:56,913
-什么？  -在森林外
{\fscx80\fscy80}- What? - Out in the woods.{\r}

538
00:45:56,984 --> 00:46:00,750
噢，给你.一块蓝莓松饼 换一只兔子.合理吧？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Oh, here you are. One muffin for one rabbit. Fair enough?{\r}

539
00:46:00,855 --> 00:46:02,686
应该是两块松饼换一只兔子
{\fscx80\fscy80}That was a two-muffin rabbit.{\r}

540
00:46:04,759 --> 00:46:07,250
-我得走了  -噢
{\fscx80\fscy80}- I gotta go now. - Oh.{\r}

541
00:46:16,104 --> 00:46:18,072
嗯
{\fscx80\fscy80}Hmm.{\r}

542
00:46:19,807 --> 00:46:24,608
今天下午的天气不错啊 格勒夫利小姐
{\fscx80\fscy80}It's, uh, certainly a nice afternoon, Miss Gravely.{\r}

543
00:46:24,679 --> 00:46:27,580
-是吧？ -嗯
{\fscx80\fscy80}Isn't it? Mmm.{\r}

544
00:46:27,682 --> 00:46:31,641
还有，你也是位漂亮的女人
{\fscx80\fscy80}Yes, and you're... You're a nice woman.{\r}

545
00:46:31,719 --> 00:46:35,211
我觉得你也挺英俊 怀尔斯船长
{\fscx80\fscy80}And I think you're awfully nice, Capt. Wiles.{\r}

546
00:46:35,289 --> 00:46:40,591
噢，我们还是回到我们的话题： 哈里
{\fscx80\fscy80}Um, um. Let's get back to our little problem Harry.{\r}

547
00:46:40,695 --> 00:46:43,960
-他怎样啦？ -噢，现在，你不用担心哈里
{\fscx80\fscy80}What's going to become of him? Oh, now, now. Don't you worry about Harry.{\r}

548
00:46:44,031 --> 00:46:46,329
他在黄昏前会安稳地埋下地里
{\fscx80\fscy80}He'll be comfortably underground before nightfall.{\r}

549
00:46:46,401 --> 00:46:51,100
都是些挖啊，凿啊的工作 你怎么不…
{\fscx80\fscy80}All that digging and work. Couldn't you just...{\r}

550
00:46:51,205 --> 00:46:54,106
让他从你的船里滑进水池里？
{\fscx80\fscy80}let him slide off the end of your boat pier into the pond?{\r}

551
00:46:56,411 --> 00:46:59,437
让他像根木头一样浮起来吗？ 不行
{\fscx80\fscy80}And have him pop up like a cork? No, sir.{\r}

552
00:46:59,514 --> 00:47:01,914
没人能在离地面4英尺处浮起来
{\fscx80\fscy80}Nobody ever popped up from under four feet of ground.{\r}

553
00:47:02,016 --> 00:47:05,645
不行 ，而且冬天他们还会在那儿挖雪
{\fscx80\fscy80}No. Besides, they'll be cutting ice there this winter.{\r}

554
00:47:05,720 --> 00:47:08,655
现在如果他们去取冰 就不太妙了
{\fscx80\fscy80}Now wouldn't it be a nice thing if they were cutting blocks of ice and...{\r}

555
00:47:08,723 --> 00:47:11,624
别紧张，船长.你说的是对的
{\fscx80\fscy80}Never mind, Captain. You're right.{\r}

556
00:47:13,528 --> 00:47:15,860
对，埋在地下对哈里 来说是最好的了
{\fscx80\fscy80}Yes. Underground is the best place for Harry.{\r}

557
00:47:42,290 --> 00:47:45,817
他看上去很舒坦，非常的舒坦
{\fscx80\fscy80}He seems comfortable, Sam, very comfortable and snug.{\r}

558
00:47:45,893 --> 00:47:48,418
我们最好找个地方，尽早挖了
{\fscx80\fscy80}We better find a place and get it dug and the sooner the better.{\r}

559
00:47:48,496 --> 00:47:51,294
如果你告诉罗杰斯夫人 和她的丈夫是正确的
{\fscx80\fscy80}If what you're telling me about Mrs. Rogers and her husband is right,{\r}

560
00:47:51,365 --> 00:47:53,356
我同意你，山姆
{\fscx80\fscy80}I agree with you, Sammy.{\r}

561
00:47:53,401 --> 00:47:55,869
噢，我们找块地方吧
{\fscx80\fscy80}Well, let's find a place.{\r}

562
00:47:55,970 --> 00:47:57,870
不用干得太辛苦的
{\fscx80\fscy80}No use making hard work out of it.{\r}

563
00:47:57,972 --> 00:47:59,872
我们要找块泥土松软的地方
{\fscx80\fscy80}We need a place where the earth is soft.{\r}

564
00:47:59,974 --> 00:48:03,535
对，找一个全镇人在我们挖掘时 都不会干扰我们的地方
{\fscx80\fscy80}Yeah, and a place where the whole town won't stumble over us as we work.{\r}

565
00:48:03,611 --> 00:48:07,570
嗯，一个极具个性的漂亮地方
{\fscx80\fscy80}Mmm. A place with a certain character and attractiveness.{\r}

566
00:48:07,615 --> 00:48:10,914
朝西的.这样哈里就可以看到日落
{\fscx80\fscy80}Facing west so that Harry can watch the setting sun.{\r}

567
00:48:10,985 --> 00:48:14,113
-冬天暖和  -而且夏天凉爽
{\fscx80\fscy80}Where it'll be cozy in winter. And cool in the summer.{\r}

568
00:48:14,188 --> 00:48:17,783
说实在，我可真有点羡慕哈里了
{\fscx80\fscy80}You know, I'm half envying Harry.{\r}

569
00:48:17,892 --> 00:48:20,861
挖两倍的宽不会花太多时间
{\fscx80\fscy80}It wouldn't take much longer to dig it twice as wide.{\r}

570
00:48:20,928 --> 00:48:23,726
谢谢你的好意，另找时间吧
{\fscx80\fscy80}Well, thanks for your kindness, but some other time.{\r}

571
00:48:29,337 --> 00:48:32,238
-这里.看来这儿可是个好地方 -啊
{\fscx80\fscy80}Here. This looks like a good place. Ah.{\r}

572
00:48:32,306 --> 00:48:34,570
你可真幸运，哈里.沃普
{\fscx80\fscy80}You're a lucky fellow, Harry Worp.{\r}

573
00:48:40,214 --> 00:48:42,910
-来吧，船长.脱掉你外衣 -为什么要我来？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Come on, Captain. Off with your coat. What, me?{\r}

574
00:48:43,017 --> 00:48:44,917
当然是你啦.这可是你人 对吧？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Certainly you. It's your body, isn't it?{\r}

575
00:48:45,019 --> 00:48:47,180
噢，我不是很善于挖坟墓
{\fscx80\fscy80}Oh, I'm not much of a hand at grave digging.{\r}

576
00:48:47,255 --> 00:48:50,486
你今天去打猎时 就该好好想想了
{\fscx80\fscy80}You should've thought of that before you went hunting this morning.{\r}

577
00:48:53,728 --> 00:48:56,959
加尔文.维格斯 我们现在如何是好？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Calvin Wiggs. What'll we do now?{\r}

578
00:48:57,031 --> 00:48:59,329
捏造一个他信以为真的故事
{\fscx80\fscy80}Think up the best story he's ever heard.{\r}

579
00:49:23,991 --> 00:49:27,757
-别挖了，山姆 -怎么了？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Lay down your shovel, Sam. What's the trouble?{\r}

580
00:49:27,862 --> 00:49:32,822
-我累得不行了 -好的.我10分钟前就累得不行了
{\fscx80\fscy80}- I'm dead beat. - Good. I was dead beat ten minutes ago.{\r}

581
00:49:32,900 --> 00:49:35,494
我想一直地挖直到你放弃
{\fscx80\fscy80}I wanted to keep digging until you gave up.{\r}

582
00:49:42,076 --> 00:49:44,977
-让我直起疙瘩 -是吗？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Gives me the creeps. Yeah?{\r}

583
00:49:45,012 --> 00:49:47,708
来吧，去抬哈里把他放进去
{\fscx80\fscy80}Come on. Let's get Harry and pop him in.{\r}

584
00:49:54,522 --> 00:49:56,490
有怪莫怪啦
{\fscx80\fscy80}With hasty reverence.{\r}

585
00:50:04,898 --> 00:50:08,459
-你想说点什么吗？船长 -当然
{\fscx80\fscy80}Would you like to say a few words, Captain? That I would.{\r}

586
00:50:08,535 --> 00:50:11,902
哈里.沃普 可别在这儿露面了！
{\fscx80\fscy80}Harry Worp, don't ever show your face around here again!{\r}

587
00:50:16,610 --> 00:50:19,306
我们弄完就走吧
{\fscx80\fscy80}Let's finish this job and get out of here.{\r}

588
00:50:19,413 --> 00:50:23,247
船长，我想加尔文.维格斯 好像在找什么
{\fscx80\fscy80}Captain, I think Calvin Wiggs is looking for something.{\r}

589
00:50:23,317 --> 00:50:25,251
你认为他是否知道 哈里.沃普到过这儿？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Do you suppose he knows that Harry Worp came up here?{\r}

590
00:50:25,319 --> 00:50:28,516
山姆，这和你想得那样可怕
{\fscx80\fscy80}Sammy, that's as horrible a thought as you've ever had.{\r}

591
00:50:28,622 --> 00:50:30,852
他会否想知道哈里怎么了 或者他在哪儿？
{\fscx80\fscy80}And that he wonders what happened to Harry or where he is?{\r}

592
00:50:30,924 --> 00:50:35,725
我的唯一答案是我们快点完工
{\fscx80\fscy80}My only answer is to keep on scraping, and fast.{\r}

593
00:50:35,762 --> 00:50:39,721
如果你还想枪杀什么 我希望你还是杀兔子吧
{\fscx80\fscy80}You know if, if you must kill things from now on, I wish you'd stick to rabbits.{\r}

594
00:50:39,766 --> 00:50:42,667
-尸体会小点-兔子！ 我可没对你说过，是吧？山姆
{\fscx80\fscy80}The body's smaller. Rabbits! I didn't tell you, did I, Sammy?{\r}

595
00:50:42,736 --> 00:50:47,230
-我今天是杀了野兔！ 别太大声了.我知道是干的
{\fscx80\fscy80}I shot a rabbit today! Don't shout. I know you did.{\r}

596
00:50:47,341 --> 00:50:50,242
我到詹尼弗.罗杰斯那儿时 安尼卡给我看的
{\fscx80\fscy80}I was up at Jennifer Rogers' when Arnie showed me the rabbit.{\r}

597
00:50:50,277 --> 00:50:53,974
詹尼弗？别浪费时间了，对吧？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Jennifer, eh? Didn't waste much time, did you?{\r}

598
00:50:54,047 --> 00:50:55,981
噢，我并没责怪你，山姆
{\fscx80\fscy80}Well, I don't blame you, Sammy.{\r}

599
00:50:56,049 --> 00:50:58,643
她是个非常好的寡妇 非常的好
{\fscx80\fscy80}A very nice widow she'll make. Very nice.{\r}

600
00:50:58,752 --> 00:51:00,947
我们埋完哈里后再说她吧？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Let's discuss her when we've finished with Harry, huh?{\r}

601
00:51:01,054 --> 00:51:03,750
别发火.我可不想说你的事
{\fscx80\fscy80}No need to get huffy. I don't want to talk about your affairs.{\r}

602
00:51:03,857 --> 00:51:06,257
我有我自己的事
{\fscx80\fscy80}I've got affairs of my own.{\r}

603
00:51:06,293 --> 00:51:08,261
你是指我的受保护人？
{\fscx80\fscy80}You mean my protege?{\r}

604
00:51:08,295 --> 00:51:10,559
-什么？  -格勒夫利小姐
{\fscx80\fscy80}Come again? Miss Gravely.{\r}

605
00:51:10,664 --> 00:51:13,861
今天下午我在维格斯夫人 的店里给她改头换面
{\fscx80\fscy80}The lady that I renovated down at Mrs. Wiggs' this afternoon.{\r}

606
00:51:13,967 --> 00:51:16,868
一个非常棒的改变
{\fscx80\fscy80}A most remarkable reversion to femininity.{\r}

607
00:51:16,904 --> 00:51:19,304
我不是很明白，山姆
{\fscx80\fscy80}I don't quite get you, Sammy boy.{\r}

608
00:51:19,373 --> 00:51:21,898
她非常兴高采烈地 去了百货店
{\fscx80\fscy80}She came into the Emporium in rather high excitement.{\r}

609
00:51:21,975 --> 00:51:25,172
想买个新的茶杯和杯垫 还有其它东西
{\fscx80\fscy80}Wanted a new cup and saucer, lots of other things.{\r}

610
00:51:25,279 --> 00:51:28,578
我给她改了个新形象 和做了新发型
{\fscx80\fscy80}I gave her a new makeup and hairdo.{\r}

611
00:51:28,682 --> 00:51:30,946
别告诉我你没注意到
{\fscx80\fscy80}Don't tell me you didn't notice.{\r}

612
00:51:31,018 --> 00:51:34,146
她是位非常友善的女士 非常的友善
{\fscx80\fscy80}She's a very nice lady, Sam. Very nice.{\r}

613
00:51:34,221 --> 00:51:37,816
我们都很友善.我不知道 有谁会像我们这样来帮忙
{\fscx80\fscy80}We're all nice. I don't see how anyone could help but like us.{\r}

614
00:51:37,891 --> 00:51:40,086
这是我今天感受到的
{\fscx80\fscy80}[Sighs] That's just how I feel today.{\r}

615
00:51:40,194 --> 00:51:42,526
我不知道我是否动心了还是…
{\fscx80\fscy80}I don't know whether I've grown rose-colored glasses or if...{\r}

616
00:51:42,596 --> 00:51:44,530
还是你爱上她了？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Or, uh, if you're in love?{\r}

617
00:51:44,598 --> 00:51:46,725
啊！
{\fscx80\fscy80}Aha! [Chuckling]{\r}

618
00:51:46,800 --> 00:51:49,928
没有什么比你知道自己 恋爱了更让人兴奋的了
{\fscx80\fscy80}There's nothing like finding yourself in love.{\r}

619
00:51:50,003 --> 00:51:52,494
会给你工作带来更多的热情
{\fscx80\fscy80}No, it adds zest to your work.{\r}

620
00:51:52,606 --> 00:51:55,006
热情！热情！
{\fscx80\fscy80}Zest! Zest!{\r}

621
00:51:55,042 --> 00:51:58,239
我想我是够热情了
{\fscx80\fscy80}I think I've had enough zest for a while.{\r}

622
00:51:58,312 --> 00:52:02,339
-我们坐下来休息一会吧？ -好的，也是时候了
{\fscx80\fscy80}Let's sit down and rest, huh? Why not? We've earned it.{\r}

623
00:52:05,519 --> 00:52:10,422
告诉我，山姆 詹尼弗对此事有何看法？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Tell me, Sam, what did Jennifer think of my shooting?{\r}

624
00:52:10,524 --> 00:52:12,424
你是指罗杰斯吧？ 噢，我想现在为止…
{\fscx80\fscy80}You mean Mrs. Rogers? Oh, I think by now...{\r}

625
00:52:12,526 --> 00:52:14,756
有可以称呼她的名字吧
{\fscx80\fscy80}I'm entitled to be on a first-name basis with her.{\r}

626
00:52:14,828 --> 00:52:17,626
毕竟，我用一颗子弹让她解脱了
{\fscx80\fscy80}After all, I brought her a happy release with one bullet.{\r}

627
00:52:17,731 --> 00:52:20,666
一颗子弹？我可看到了 “监制射击”的告示啊
{\fscx80\fscy80}One bullet? How 'bout that "No Shooting" sign that I found?{\r}

628
00:52:20,734 --> 00:52:23,726
噢，用一颗子弹射 “禁止射击”的告示
{\fscx80\fscy80}Well, that. One bullet for the "No Shooting" sign,{\r}

629
00:52:23,770 --> 00:52:26,671
一颗射啤酒罐还有一颗射哈里
{\fscx80\fscy80}one for the beer can and one for Harry.{\r}

630
00:52:26,740 --> 00:52:29,436
-那么野兔呢？ 一颗射野…
{\fscx80\fscy80}How about the rabbit? And one for the ra...{\r}

631
00:52:34,381 --> 00:52:36,349
怎么了？
{\fscx80\fscy80}What's the matter?{\r}

632
00:52:36,450 --> 00:52:38,350
怎么了？什么咬了你？
{\fscx80\fscy80}What's wrong? What's bitten you?{\r}

633
00:52:38,452 --> 00:52:41,012
我只是射了三枪.三枪！
{\fscx80\fscy80}I only fired three bullets. Three!{\r}

634
00:52:41,088 --> 00:52:43,750
一枪射了告示牌 一枪射了啤酒罐
{\fscx80\fscy80}One for the shooting sign, one for the beer can...{\r}

635
00:52:43,857 --> 00:52:46,052
一枪射了躺在坟墓里的人
{\fscx80\fscy80}And one for the little man who's lying in the grave.{\r}

636
00:52:46,159 --> 00:52:48,753
没有，没有.一枪射中了野兔
{\fscx80\fscy80}No, Sammy, no. That's just it. One for the rabbit.{\r}

637
00:52:48,862 --> 00:52:51,262
如果我射了野兔 哈里就不是我射死的
{\fscx80\fscy80}If I shot the rabbit, I didn't shoot Harry.{\r}

638
00:52:51,298 --> 00:52:54,267
噢，山姆，你本意是什么？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Oh, Sammy boy, what have you tried to make me do?{\r}

639
00:52:54,368 --> 00:52:56,268
不就是不让我 背杀人犯的黑锅吗
{\fscx80\fscy80}Tried to make a murderer out of me.{\r}

640
00:52:58,472 --> 00:53:02,602
好了，别坐那儿了.帮忙啊！ 你帮了我埋了他
{\fscx80\fscy80}Well, don't sit there. Help me! You helped bury him.{\r}

641
00:53:02,676 --> 00:53:05,042
如果不是你杀的 那你为什么要来埋他
{\fscx80\fscy80}Even if you didn't kill him, why go digging him up...{\r}

642
00:53:05,112 --> 00:53:07,205
现在不是干得挺妥当的吗？
{\fscx80\fscy80}now that he's so beautifully planted?{\r}

643
00:53:07,281 --> 00:53:09,875
我答应过詹尼弗 我们会把他埋了
{\fscx80\fscy80}I've promised Jennifer that we'd bury him.{\r}

644
00:53:09,983 --> 00:53:12,952
我要受信用，他得躺在下面
{\fscx80\fscy80}Keep my word, he should stay buried.{\r}

645
00:53:13,020 --> 00:53:15,853
而且不管是否是你杀他的 你已经控诉过自己了
{\fscx80\fscy80}Besides whether you killed him or not, you've incriminated yourself.{\r}

646
00:53:15,922 --> 00:53:20,291
你这样要去解释你没杀 这个人却又要埋他
{\fscx80\fscy80}You'll have more of a job explaining away a body you didn't kill and buried...{\r}

647
00:53:20,327 --> 00:53:23,296
比你去解释你无意杀了个人 然后把他埋更麻烦
{\fscx80\fscy80}than a body that you killed accidentally and buried.{\r}

648
00:53:23,330 --> 00:53:26,231
对吧，船长？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Right, Captain?{\r}

649
00:53:29,903 --> 00:53:32,303
你找到他时不该想要埋了他
{\fscx80\fscy80}You're not supposed to bury bodies whenever you find them.{\r}

650
00:53:32,406 --> 00:53:34,306
这让别人起疑心
{\fscx80\fscy80}It makes people suspicious.{\r}

651
00:53:34,408 --> 00:53:36,876
似乎也对警察透露了什么 或表明了什么
{\fscx80\fscy80}Supposed to tell the police or advertise or something.{\r}

652
00:53:36,943 --> 00:53:40,902
噢，山姆，你是不明白的 你根本不理解
{\fscx80\fscy80}Oh, Sammy, you don't understand. You don't comprehend one bit.{\r}

653
00:53:41,014 --> 00:53:44,313
你应该不想我余生 就这样不明不白的过吧？
{\fscx80\fscy80}You wouldn't like me to go through my life not knowing if I killed him or not, would you?{\r}

654
00:53:47,020 --> 00:53:49,147
真是矛盾
{\fscx80\fscy80}Very inconsistent.{\r}

655
00:53:49,222 --> 00:53:51,247
之前你说你问心无愧
{\fscx80\fscy80}First you tell me you've got no conscience.{\r}

656
00:53:51,325 --> 00:53:53,987
现在你说得又好像良心发现
{\fscx80\fscy80}Now you talk about something that sounds remarkably like a conscience.{\r}

657
00:53:54,061 --> 00:53:56,052
噢，山姆，过来帮我一把吧
{\fscx80\fscy80}Oh, Sammy, come on. Help me.{\r}

658
00:53:56,129 --> 00:53:59,257
其实我并不关心 是否是我杀了他
{\fscx80\fscy80}I don't care if I killed him or not, for all that matters.{\r}

659
00:53:59,333 --> 00:54:04,293
但我一见到警察就抖 说我没干过又不好受
{\fscx80\fscy80}But I'll get the shakes whenever I see a policeman, and it's no good saying I won't.{\r}

660
00:54:04,371 --> 00:54:06,339
好了
{\fscx80\fscy80}All right.{\r}

661
00:54:06,440 --> 00:54:10,035
如果是我，我宁愿被误认 是杀人犯也不愿去证明山姆
{\fscx80\fscy80}If I had my choice, I'd rather be thought a murderer than proved one.{\r}

662
00:54:10,143 --> 00:54:14,375
我们俩一起挖，我们就能 很省事就把哈里挖出来了
{\fscx80\fscy80}With two of us digging, we'll have Harry out of here in nothing flat.{\r}

663
00:54:22,289 --> 00:54:24,280
这儿看得不清楚
{\fscx80\fscy80}Can't see much from here.{\r}

664
00:54:24,358 --> 00:54:26,383
我还是得趴下看看
{\fscx80\fscy80}I'd better get in down there and look at him.{\r}

665
00:54:26,460 --> 00:54:30,123
-让我来代劳吧 -好的，你的眼睛好使
{\fscx80\fscy80}Let me do the honors. All right. You've got good eyes.{\r}

666
00:54:32,065 --> 00:54:35,228
嘿，那不是子弹伤的
{\fscx80\fscy80}Hey. That isn't a bullet wound.{\r}

667
00:54:35,302 --> 00:54:37,361
-不是子弹伤的？ -不是
{\fscx80\fscy80}"Isn't a bullet wound"? No.{\r}

668
00:54:37,471 --> 00:54:39,371
你怎么知道？
{\fscx80\fscy80}What d'ya know?{\r}

669
00:54:39,473 --> 00:54:42,203
那拿硬物打伤的
{\fscx80\fscy80}That's what they call a blow with a blunt instrument.{\r}

670
00:54:42,275 --> 00:54:44,971
噢？你有什么看法，山姆？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Huh? What are you thinking, Sammy?{\r}

671
00:54:46,780 --> 00:54:50,807
我想，怀尔斯船长 遇到了一宗谋杀
{\fscx80\fscy80}I think, Capt. Wiles, we're tangled up in a murder.{\r}

672
00:54:50,884 --> 00:54:54,786
谋杀.如果是谋杀，是谁干的？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Murder. If it's murder, who done it?{\r}

673
00:54:54,888 --> 00:54:58,551
-是谁干的？ -我刚才不是问过了：是谁干的？
{\fscx80\fscy80}- Who "did" it? - That's what I say Who done it?{\r}

674
00:54:58,625 --> 00:55:02,152
除了詹尼弗.罗杰斯 还会有谁想杀他？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Apart from Jennifer Rogers, who else'd want to kill him?{\r}

675
00:55:03,597 --> 00:55:05,497
除了詹尼弗？
{\fscx80\fscy80}"Apart from Jennifer"?{\r}

676
00:55:05,599 --> 00:55:07,499
对，你认为她会否…
{\fscx80\fscy80}Yeah. Do you think that she would...{\r}

677
00:55:07,601 --> 00:55:09,501
噢，荒谬
{\fscx80\fscy80}Oh, it's ridiculous.{\r}

678
00:55:09,603 --> 00:55:12,094
你说过当她来到这儿 看到死尸时，她很惊讶的
{\fscx80\fscy80}You said she was surprised to see the body when she came up here.{\r}

679
00:55:12,205 --> 00:55:14,730
你不也说过她敲打过他的头吗
{\fscx80\fscy80}You said she hit him on the head.{\r}

680
00:55:14,808 --> 00:55:17,299
加岛来，船上会有渔夫…
{\fscx80\fscy80}Coming home from Madagascar once, we had a fireman on board...{\r}

681
00:55:17,411 --> 00:55:20,141
用砖头敲了他的头 接着两天后就死了
{\fscx80\fscy80}who hit his head on a brick wall and died two days later.{\r}

682
00:55:20,213 --> 00:55:22,647
他在穿上哪儿能找到砖头？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Where could he find a brick wall on board a ship?{\r}

683
00:55:22,716 --> 00:55:25,708
这也是我们都疑惑的
{\fscx80\fscy80}That's what we always wondered.{\r}

684
00:55:27,120 --> 00:55:30,715
不会是詹尼弗的，不是
{\fscx80\fscy80}[Sighs] Couldn't have been Jennifer. No.{\r}

685
00:55:30,824 --> 00:55:33,156
而且谁干的又有什么关系？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Besides, what's it matter who did it?{\r}

686
00:55:33,226 --> 00:55:35,660
如果把他埋了眼不见心不烦 对我们大家都有好处
{\fscx80\fscy80}It'll be better for all of us if he's buried and out of the way.{\r}

687
00:55:35,729 --> 00:55:39,631
不行 我可不来收拾别人的烂摊子
{\fscx80\fscy80}Nothing doing. I'm not burying someone else's bad habits.{\r}

688
00:55:39,666 --> 00:55:42,191
呃？或许是格勒夫利小姐干的？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Hmm? Suppose it was Miss Gravely?{\r}

689
00:55:42,269 --> 00:55:45,568
什么？
{\fscx80\fscy80}What? [Laughing]{\r}

690
00:55:45,639 --> 00:55:48,130
一点也不好笑
{\fscx80\fscy80}No, it's not as funny as all that.{\r}

691
00:55:48,241 --> 00:55:50,573
是你自己说她见到哈里时…
{\fscx80\fscy80}You said yourself she wasn't particularly startled...{\r}

692
00:55:50,644 --> 00:55:52,578
不感到惊讶的
{\fscx80\fscy80}to see you dragging Harry up the path.{\r}

693
00:55:52,646 --> 00:55:55,740
你这个艺术家一点礼貌都没有
{\fscx80\fscy80}You artists have got no idea of etiquette.{\r}

694
00:55:55,849 --> 00:55:58,317
格勒夫利小姐秉性温柔 而且有教养
{\fscx80\fscy80}Miss Gravely is a lady of gentle habits and upbringing.{\r}

695
00:55:58,385 --> 00:56:01,354
一位内敛的女士 如果不是我拖着哈里
{\fscx80\fscy80}A lady to hide her feelings. If I hadn't been holding Harry by the ankles,{\r}

696
00:56:01,455 --> 00:56:03,548
我想她根本不会说什么
{\fscx80\fscy80}I don't suppose she'd have mentioned him at all.{\r}

697
00:56:03,657 --> 00:56:06,888
-真的？  -啊！当她说
{\fscx80\fscy80}- Really? - Nah! When she said,{\r}

698
00:56:06,960 --> 00:56:09,451
“怎么啦，船长？”
{\fscx80\fscy80}"What seems to be the trouble, Captain?"{\r}

699
00:56:09,563 --> 00:56:11,963
说得非常的畅心，就好像在说
{\fscx80\fscy80}It was nothing more than a pleasantry, so to speak.{\r}

700
00:56:12,065 --> 00:56:16,092
“今天天气不错啊，是吧？” “我想是的”
{\fscx80\fscy80}Like, "Nice day, isn't it?" "I'm sure, yes."{\r}

701
00:56:16,169 --> 00:56:18,103
或其它什么的
{\fscx80\fscy80}Or something like that.{\r}

702
00:56:18,171 --> 00:56:20,571
想不想帮我再埋了他？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Going to help me bury him again?{\r}

703
00:56:20,674 --> 00:56:24,303
呃，不知道
{\fscx80\fscy80}Um... I don't know.{\r}

704
00:56:24,377 --> 00:56:27,778
也可能是格林保医生 或流浪汉或…
{\fscx80\fscy80}'Course, it might have been Dr. Greenbow or the tramp or...{\r}

705
00:56:27,881 --> 00:56:32,079
-或者是詹尼弗？ -我说过那不可能是…
{\fscx80\fscy80}OrJennifer? I told you it couldn't...{\r}

706
00:56:32,185 --> 00:56:35,586
噢，再争这个也没有意思了 我们安顿好他吧
{\fscx80\fscy80}Well, no point in arguing about it. Let's get rid of him.{\r}

707
00:56:37,591 --> 00:56:42,494
好的，你在我需要时帮忙 我想也是时候我帮你一把了
{\fscx80\fscy80}All right. You've helped me in my hour of need. I guess it's up to me to help you.{\r}

708
00:56:42,596 --> 00:56:45,360
-我们还是忘了哈里吧
{\fscx80\fscy80}We'll file Harry away once and for all. Yeah.{\r}

709
00:56:45,432 --> 00:56:47,400
没有比这更无稽的了
{\fscx80\fscy80}No more nonsense about it.{\r}

710
00:57:13,226 --> 00:57:16,024
请进，格勒夫利小姐，请进
{\fscx80\fscy80}Come aboard, Miss Gravely, come aboard.{\r}

711
00:57:16,129 --> 00:57:18,791
只是个又老又旧的地方
{\fscx80\fscy80}It's just an old salt's snug anchorage.{\r}

712
00:57:18,865 --> 00:57:22,596
很小，没你家那般富丽堂皇 但非常的温馨
{\fscx80\fscy80}Small, not palatial like yours. But homely, very home...{\r}

713
00:57:38,552 --> 00:57:40,543
请坐吧，格勒夫利小姐
{\fscx80\fscy80}Won't you sit down, Miss Gravely?{\r}

714
00:57:40,654 --> 00:57:42,554
谢谢
{\fscx80\fscy80}Thank you.{\r}

715
00:57:44,758 --> 00:57:49,718
真是有趣，我们就那么一个下午 就变得那么亲近了
{\fscx80\fscy80}It's funny, you know. Funny how we got to be so friendly in one afternoon.{\r}

716
00:57:49,763 --> 00:57:53,961
我知道你并非像他们那样呆板
{\fscx80\fscy80}I knew you weren't as prim and starchy as they made out.{\r}

717
00:57:54,067 --> 00:57:56,035
还是因为那次射击
{\fscx80\fscy80}[Chuckling ] Not by a long shot.{\r}

718
00:57:56,102 --> 00:57:58,070
-真的吗？     -不
{\fscx80\fscy80}Really? NO.{\r}

719
00:57:58,104 --> 00:58:01,232
我是一个能看清女性优点的男人
{\fscx80\fscy80}I'm a man who can recognize the human qualities in a woman.{\r}

720
00:58:01,308 --> 00:58:03,708
当我在哈里出事那儿见到你时
{\fscx80\fscy80}When I first saw you down where Harry was...{\r}

721
00:58:03,777 --> 00:58:06,075
-怀尔斯船长    -啊？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Capt. Wiles. Yes, ma'am?{\r}

722
00:58:06,179 --> 00:58:09,342
在你这么好意地评价我之前，我
{\fscx80\fscy80}Before you make your kind thoughts known to me, I...{\r}

723
00:58:09,416 --> 00:58:13,113
我想向你解释一下我今天下午 为什么这么突然地
{\fscx80\fscy80}should like to offer you some explanation of my sudden invitation...{\r}

724
00:58:13,186 --> 00:58:15,916
邀请你去喝咖啡吃蓝莓松饼…
{\fscx80\fscy80}to coffee and blueberry muffins this afternoon...{\r}

725
00:58:15,989 --> 00:58:19,152
还有我，我现在为什么会 和你坐在一块
{\fscx80\fscy80}and my... and my sitting with you here now.{\r}

726
00:58:19,225 --> 00:58:21,386
不，你不必解释任何东西
{\fscx80\fscy80}No, ma'am, you don't have to explain anything.{\r}

727
00:58:21,494 --> 00:58:25,555
你在我困难时帮助我，实在感激
{\fscx80\fscy80}You came to my aid at a moment of crisis, for which I'm truly grateful.{\r}

728
00:58:25,632 --> 00:58:29,932
谢谢，但这也是我觉得 亏欠你的地方
{\fscx80\fscy80}Thank you, but it's just that I owe you some reason.{\r}

729
00:58:30,003 --> 00:58:32,437
不，不，不.我可不想听你这样说
{\fscx80\fscy80}No, no, no. I won't hear a word of it.{\r}

730
00:58:32,505 --> 00:58:35,906
你目睹了我处置那尸体时的窘态
{\fscx80\fscy80}You saw the predicament I was in with that body on my hands and all,{\r}

731
00:58:35,942 --> 00:58:39,605
而你却非常友善地谅解了我
{\fscx80\fscy80}and you shut your eyes to it in a most sporting fashion, if I may say so.{\r}

732
00:58:39,713 --> 00:58:42,011
-怀尔斯船长   -怎么了？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Capt. Wiles. Yes, ma'am?{\r}

733
00:58:42,115 --> 00:58:46,074
我要告诉你我请你去喝咖啡 和吃蓝莓饼的原因
{\fscx80\fscy80}I'm trying to tell you that the reason I asked you to coffee and blueberry muffins...{\r}

734
00:58:46,152 --> 00:58:48,620
是因为…我觉得…
{\fscx80\fscy80}was because... I felt...{\r}

735
00:58:48,655 --> 00:58:50,850
-同情我    -感谢你
{\fscx80\fscy80}Sympathy. Gratitude.{\r}

736
00:58:50,924 --> 00:58:53,859
感…但应该是我感谢你才对的
{\fscx80\fscy80}Gra... But I'm the one who should be grateful.{\r}

737
00:58:53,927 --> 00:58:58,887
不，我该感谢你.我感激你
{\fscx80\fscy80}No, I was grateful. L... I am grateful.{\r}

738
00:58:58,932 --> 00:59:03,062
我感激你帮忙 把我所杀的人给埋了
{\fscx80\fscy80}I'm grateful to you for burying my body.{\r}

739
00:59:08,341 --> 00:59:10,275
你杀的人？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Your body?{\r}

740
00:59:10,343 --> 00:59:12,937
那个你以为是你自己杀的人…
{\fscx80\fscy80}The man you thought you killed...{\r}

741
00:59:13,046 --> 00:59:17,449
是被我用高跟皮鞋砸他的 脑袋而死的
{\fscx80\fscy80}was the man I hit over the head with the leather heel of my hiking shoe.{\r}

742
00:59:17,484 --> 00:59:19,748
你？
{\fscx80\fscy80}You?{\r}

743
00:59:19,853 --> 00:59:23,050
-最后还用了铁板  -为什么
{\fscx80\fscy80}- And with a metal cleat on the end of it. - But why?{\r}

744
00:59:24,958 --> 00:59:26,892
他骚扰我
{\fscx80\fscy80}He annoyed me.{\r}

745
00:59:26,960 --> 00:59:29,554
我回家时，这时他…
{\fscx80\fscy80}I was walking towards home when he...{\r}

746
00:59:29,663 --> 00:59:32,154
突然冒了出来，眼神怪怪的…
{\fscx80\fscy80}suddenly came at me with a wild look in his eye...{\r}

747
00:59:32,265 --> 00:59:35,393
并胡扯说我们结婚了
{\fscx80\fscy80}and insisted... we were married.{\r}

748
00:59:35,468 --> 00:59:37,766
噢，之前你们都认识的
{\fscx80\fscy80}Oh, then you'd known each other before.{\r}

749
00:59:37,871 --> 00:59:40,897
相信也好，不相信也罢 我之前从未见过他
{\fscx80\fscy80}Believe it or not, I had never seen him before in my life,{\r}

750
00:59:40,974 --> 00:59:44,910
即使是见过他 我也肯定不会和他结婚
{\fscx80\fscy80}and... if I ever had, I never would have married him.{\r}

751
00:59:44,978 --> 00:59:47,469
他肯定误以为你是其他人了
{\fscx80\fscy80}He must have mistaken you for someone else.{\r}

752
00:59:47,580 --> 00:59:51,516
不，他应该不会… 他拉着我到矮树林
{\fscx80\fscy80}No, he definitely... pulled me into the bushes.{\r}

753
00:59:51,584 --> 00:59:53,677
是吗？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Yes?{\r}

754
00:59:53,787 --> 00:59:57,951
-我挣扎出来了   -继续
{\fscx80\fscy80}- I came out again. - Go on.{\r}

755
00:59:58,024 --> 01:00:01,585
他又拉我回去了
{\fscx80\fscy80}He pulled me back.{\r}

756
01:00:01,695 --> 01:00:03,595
两次啊
{\fscx80\fscy80}Twice.{\r}

757
01:00:03,697 --> 01:00:07,189
他用非常可怕 非常硬朗的声音对我说话
{\fscx80\fscy80}He swore at me... horrible, masculine sounds.{\r}

758
01:00:07,300 --> 01:00:09,200
我当然不知道他在说什么
{\fscx80\fscy80}I didn't understand them, of course.{\r}

759
01:00:09,302 --> 01:00:12,271
那是肯定的
{\fscx80\fscy80}Of course you didn't.{\r}

760
01:00:12,338 --> 01:00:14,863
-我们打了起来 -然后呢？
{\fscx80\fscy80}- We fought. - Then what?{\r}

761
01:00:16,309 --> 01:00:21,269
我赢了.我的鞋子在挣扎过程中 掉了出来.我就敲了他
{\fscx80\fscy80}I won. My shoe had come off in the struggle, and I hit him.{\r}

762
01:00:21,347 --> 01:00:24,874
我往死里敲他
{\fscx80\fscy80}I hit him as hard as ever I could.{\r}

763
01:00:28,054 --> 01:00:30,022
你杀了他
{\fscx80\fscy80}You killed him.{\r}

764
01:00:31,458 --> 01:00:35,622
我不得不这样.我被他骚扰了 船长
{\fscx80\fscy80}I must have done it. I was annoyed, Captain.{\r}

765
01:00:36,763 --> 01:00:38,958
-非常的不礼貌 -那很自然
{\fscx80\fscy80}Very annoyed. Naturally.{\r}

766
01:00:39,032 --> 01:00:42,297
我想我可从未受过这样的骚扰
{\fscx80\fscy80}I don't think I've ever been so annoyed.{\r}

767
01:00:42,368 --> 01:00:47,237
结果我就失去理智了
{\fscx80\fscy80}Consequently, I, I didn't realize my own capabilities.{\r}

768
01:00:47,340 --> 01:00:50,673
噢！在我看来…
{\fscx80\fscy80}Whew! Seems to me...{\r}

769
01:00:50,744 --> 01:00:53,736
罗杰斯夫人傻乎乎地敲了他 你却完结了他
{\fscx80\fscy80}Mrs. Rogers knocked him silly, and you finished him off.{\r}

770
01:00:53,847 --> 01:00:56,816
为什么罗杰斯夫人要敲他？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Why should Mrs. Rogers knock him silly?{\r}

771
01:00:56,883 --> 01:00:59,215
她才是他的妻子
{\fscx80\fscy80}She was really his wife.{\r}

772
01:00:59,285 --> 01:01:03,881
可怜的女人 我想她的品味独特
{\fscx80\fscy80}Poor woman. I thought she had better taste.{\r}

773
01:01:05,558 --> 01:01:07,492
你知道吗，船长
{\fscx80\fscy80}You know, Captain,{\r}

774
01:01:07,560 --> 01:01:11,553
我逃跑后，我就决定我永远 不会对其他人说这事
{\fscx80\fscy80}when I ran away I decided I would never tell a soul what happened.{\r}

775
01:01:11,664 --> 01:01:14,258
接着我遇见了你，我想…
{\fscx80\fscy80}Then I met you, and I thought...{\r}

776
01:01:14,367 --> 01:01:19,669
你认为这是你杀的 这真是太好不过了
{\fscx80\fscy80}how convenient it was that you should think that you had shot him.{\r}

777
01:01:19,773 --> 01:01:23,106
-请你原谅我这么想 -挺自然的
{\fscx80\fscy80}- You must forgive me for thinking that. - Only natural.{\r}

778
01:01:23,176 --> 01:01:27,806
这就是为什么我觉得亏欠了你
{\fscx80\fscy80}That's why I felt... I still feel under an obligation to you.{\r}

779
01:01:27,881 --> 01:01:30,782
噢，别提了.我们忘了它吧
{\fscx80\fscy80}Oh, not at all. Let's forget it.{\r}

780
01:01:30,884 --> 01:01:34,718
不行，我们不能这样做 这对你不公平
{\fscx80\fscy80}No, we mustn't do that. It would hardly be fair to you...{\r}

781
01:01:34,788 --> 01:01:39,782
我是指你埋了不是你杀的人
{\fscx80\fscy80}I mean, for you to go through life knowing that you had buried a man you didn't kill.{\r}

782
01:01:39,893 --> 01:01:42,361
你帮我顶替了罪行
{\fscx80\fscy80}You would have my crime on your conscience.{\r}

783
01:01:42,428 --> 01:01:45,397
是我的荣幸，噢.不好意思
{\fscx80\fscy80}It's a pleasure, [Hiccups] I'm sure.{\r}

784
01:01:45,431 --> 01:01:47,558
别这样
{\fscx80\fscy80}But no.{\r}

785
01:01:47,634 --> 01:01:51,593
现在我意识到 哈里这个人已经完全丧失理智
{\fscx80\fscy80}Now I realize that Harry man was out of his mind, and...{\r}

786
01:01:51,638 --> 01:01:54,300
而我说做的代表正义
{\fscx80\fscy80}my action was justifiable,{\r}

787
01:01:54,407 --> 01:01:57,376
没理由我们不让警方知道
{\fscx80\fscy80}there's no reason we shouldn't let the authorities know about it.{\r}

788
01:01:57,443 --> 01:02:01,004
-警方？ -这样一切都真相大白了
{\fscx80\fscy80}The authorities? Then everything will be cleared up nicely.{\r}

789
01:02:01,114 --> 01:02:03,912
我想加尔文.维格斯 和那些警察
{\fscx80\fscy80}I'm sure Calvin Wiggs and the police...{\r}

790
01:02:04,017 --> 01:02:06,542
不会对我们的解释有所疑惑
{\fscx80\fscy80}won't make a fuss about it when we explain.{\r}

791
01:02:06,619 --> 01:02:09,918
-或许还不用被记入案底 -别天真了，夫人
{\fscx80\fscy80}Perhaps it needn't get into the papers at all. Don't you believe it, ma'am.{\r}

792
01:02:10,023 --> 01:02:12,355
这可是他们所喜欢的素材 案底
{\fscx80\fscy80}They love it, the papers, this kind of thing.{\r}

793
01:02:12,425 --> 01:02:14,916
谋杀，动机
{\fscx80\fscy80}Murder and passion.{\r}

794
01:02:15,028 --> 01:02:17,622
你就别管哈里了 忘了所发生的一切吧
{\fscx80\fscy80}You let Harry be. Just forget it ever happened,{\r}

795
01:02:17,730 --> 01:02:21,530
就好像山姆，我和 詹尼弗.罗杰斯那样
{\fscx80\fscy80}the same as Sammy and me and Jennifer Rogers are going to do.{\r}

796
01:02:21,634 --> 01:02:26,230
噢，但那可不是你所杀的人啊
{\fscx80\fscy80}Oh, but... but it isn't your body.{\r}

797
01:02:26,339 --> 01:02:30,833
毕竟，他是我杀的 所以我这样说才通情达理
{\fscx80\fscy80}After all, I killed him, so it's only fair that I should have the say-so.{\r}

798
01:02:30,944 --> 01:02:33,037
-对，但… -你不这么认为吗？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Yes, but... Well, in a way... DOn't yOu agree?{\r}

799
01:02:33,146 --> 01:02:36,638
我想你是的.船长
{\fscx80\fscy80}I thought you would. I tell you what, Captain.{\r}

800
01:02:39,686 --> 01:02:42,154
-现在我们去拿把铁锹 -但，夫人…
{\fscx80\fscy80}We'll go and get a spade now. But, ma'am...{\r}

801
01:02:42,188 --> 01:02:45,055
我们把他挖出来后 我们就回到我的家
{\fscx80\fscy80}And after we've dug him up, we'll go back to my place...{\r}

802
01:02:45,158 --> 01:02:47,592
我会给你煮点热巧克力
{\fscx80\fscy80}and I'll make you some hot chocolate.{\r}

803
01:03:28,301 --> 01:03:31,600
安尼卡累得够呛了 他睡了一天一夜
{\fscx80\fscy80}Arnie's so tired he'll sleep all day and half the night.{\r}

804
01:03:31,704 --> 01:03:34,332
詹尼弗 我觉得你的房子挺漂亮的
{\fscx80\fscy80}I think you've got a pretty house,Jennifer.{\r}

805
01:03:34,407 --> 01:03:37,706
这是我用罗伯特的 保险金装修的
{\fscx80\fscy80}It's the best I could do on Robert's insurance.{\r}

806
01:03:37,810 --> 01:03:40,074
-要糖吗？  -不要，斋啡
{\fscx80\fscy80}Sugar? No, black, thanks.{\r}

807
01:03:50,657 --> 01:03:52,625
有点好笑，但…
{\fscx80\fscy80}It's funny, but...{\r}

808
01:03:52,659 --> 01:03:56,117
我觉得和你在一块挺舒服的 山姆
{\fscx80\fscy80}I feel awful comfortable with you, Sam.{\r}

809
01:03:58,364 --> 01:04:00,855
你知道吗，我也有同感
{\fscx80\fscy80}You know, I feel the same way too.{\r}

810
01:04:00,934 --> 01:04:02,925
感觉挺好的
{\fscx80\fscy80}It's a good feeling,{\r}

811
01:04:03,036 --> 01:04:06,437
能有人和自己的感觉是一样的
{\fscx80\fscy80}feeling comfortable with someone who feels that way too.{\r}

812
01:04:10,443 --> 01:04:12,934
但有件事让我挺担心的
{\fscx80\fscy80}There is one thing I feel uncomfortable about.{\r}

813
01:04:13,046 --> 01:04:16,379
告诉我，我来帮你照料
{\fscx80\fscy80}Tell me what it is, and I'll take care of it for you.{\r}

814
01:04:16,449 --> 01:04:18,383
哈里？哈里怎样了？
{\fscx80\fscy80}It's Harry? What about Harry?{\r}

815
01:04:18,451 --> 01:04:21,215
哈里？别想他了？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Harry? Don't you think about Harry.{\r}

816
01:04:21,287 --> 01:04:24,552
哈里已经归于尘土了 他成了永恒，是过去了
{\fscx80\fscy80}Harry's part of the earth. He's with eternity, the ages.{\r}

817
01:04:24,657 --> 01:04:26,852
听我的话，哈里成为历史了
{\fscx80\fscy80}Take my word for it. Harry's ancient history.{\r}

818
01:04:28,962 --> 01:04:31,123
进来吧，不管是谁
{\fscx80\fscy80}Come in, whoever it is.{\r}

819
01:04:34,600 --> 01:04:36,568
怎么啦？
{\fscx80\fscy80}What happened? [Sighs]{\r}

820
01:04:36,669 --> 01:04:39,137
山姆，我有事要告诉你
{\fscx80\fscy80}Sam, I've got Something to tell you.{\r}

821
01:04:39,205 --> 01:04:42,766
不，船长.我有事要告诉他
{\fscx80\fscy80}No, Captain, I have something to tell him.{\r}

822
01:04:42,875 --> 01:04:45,275
究竟什么事啊？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Now who's going to tell what?{\r}

823
01:04:47,380 --> 01:04:51,214
我用我的高跟鞋杀了哈里
{\fscx80\fscy80}I killed Harry Worp with the leather heel of my hiking shoe.{\r}

824
01:04:54,387 --> 01:04:57,652
-是你杀的 我们要去通知加尔文.维格斯
{\fscx80\fscy80}- So it was you. - We're on our way to get Calvin Wiggs,{\r}

825
01:04:57,724 --> 01:05:01,057
-让他通知联邦警察 我劝她这根本没必要
{\fscx80\fscy80}and have him call the state police. I keep telling her there's no need.{\r}

826
01:05:01,127 --> 01:05:05,291
他说得对，而且那样不是 很妥当.哈里死了也被埋了
{\fscx80\fscy80}He's right and, uh, besides, it'd be indecent. Harry's dead and buried.{\r}

827
01:05:05,398 --> 01:05:07,593
山姆，我有件事要告诉你
{\fscx80\fscy80}Sam, I've got something to tell you.{\r}

828
01:05:08,801 --> 01:05:10,735
你不会又挖起他了吧
{\fscx80\fscy80}You haven't dug him up again.{\r}

829
01:05:10,803 --> 01:05:12,896
噢，我…
{\fscx80\fscy80}Well, l...{\r}

830
01:05:19,712 --> 01:05:22,112
我坚持要这样做，马洛先生
{\fscx80\fscy80}I insisted, Mr. Marlow.{\r}

831
01:05:22,215 --> 01:05:24,547
你还不明白吗？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Don't you understand?{\r}

832
01:05:24,617 --> 01:05:28,917
你没必要害怕 这是我要说的
{\fscx80\fscy80}You have nothing to fear. It's my concern entirely.{\r}

833
01:05:29,022 --> 01:05:33,322
怀尔斯船长把所有情况 告诉我之后
{\fscx80\fscy80}As soon as Capt. Wiles told me the full circumstances of his being here,{\r}

834
01:05:33,359 --> 01:05:35,327
我就知道没什么 好躲躲闪闪的了
{\fscx80\fscy80}I knew there was nothing for me to hide.{\r}

835
01:05:35,361 --> 01:05:37,522
你对哈里知道多少？
{\fscx80\fscy80}You know all about Harry?{\r}

836
01:05:37,630 --> 01:05:40,030
我是知道的，罗杰斯夫人 而且…
{\fscx80\fscy80}I'm afraid I do, Mrs. Rogers, and...{\r}

837
01:05:40,066 --> 01:05:43,866
而且没人会多嘴一位女士 和疯子的事
{\fscx80\fscy80}and after all, nobody could possibly gossip about a lady and a maniac.{\r}

838
01:05:43,936 --> 01:05:45,870
你真让人意想不到
{\fscx80\fscy80}You'd be surprised.{\r}

839
01:05:45,938 --> 01:05:48,839
你可能还不知道谋杀意味着什么 格勒夫利小姐
{\fscx80\fscy80}You don't quite understand what murder involves, Miss Gravely.{\r}

840
01:05:48,875 --> 01:05:51,469
是没完没了的审问和拍照
{\fscx80\fscy80}It'd be hours and hours of questioning and photographs,{\r}

841
01:05:51,544 --> 01:05:54,536
而你的私人生活会 被报纸乱说一通
{\fscx80\fscy80}and the whole of your private life spread indecently in the newspapers.{\r}

842
01:05:56,849 --> 01:06:00,046
你怎么这样说我的私人生活 这么糟糕啊？
{\fscx80\fscy80}What makes you think my private life is indecent?{\r}

843
01:06:00,153 --> 01:06:03,281
我不是这意思 我是指他们侦查的手段很肮脏
{\fscx80\fscy80}I didn't mean that. I meant that the way they pry is indecent.{\r}

844
01:06:03,356 --> 01:06:08,020
他们恨不得你死.这就是报纸 摄影师，侦探了
{\fscx80\fscy80}They'll hound you to death. There'll be newspapermen, photographers, detectives.{\r}

845
01:06:08,094 --> 01:06:11,325
-我已经决定了 -她看起来像是了
{\fscx80\fscy80}- I've made up my mind. - She certainly has.{\r}

846
01:06:11,397 --> 01:06:14,195
是怀尔斯船长劝我
{\fscx80\fscy80}It was Capt. Wiles here who persuaded me to call...{\r}

847
01:06:14,267 --> 01:06:17,327
给罗杰斯夫人电话并告诉她 我打算如何做
{\fscx80\fscy80}and tell Mrs. Rogers what I proposed to do.{\r}

848
01:06:17,403 --> 01:06:21,499
毕竟，她和这件事也有点关系
{\fscx80\fscy80}After all, she is most closely connected with the business.{\r}

849
01:06:21,574 --> 01:06:24,407
你觉得呢，罗杰斯夫人？
{\fscx80\fscy80}What do you think about it, Mrs. Rogers?{\r}

850
01:06:24,477 --> 01:06:27,469
我不懂你们怎么把哈里 这事弄成这样
{\fscx80\fscy80}I can't see why you're all making such a fuss about Harry.{\r}

851
01:06:27,580 --> 01:06:31,141
如果他已经被埋了 我不明白你为何又要挖起他
{\fscx80\fscy80}If he was buried, I don't see why you had to dig him up.{\r}

852
01:06:31,217 --> 01:06:34,482
但既然你这样做了 我想你最好做你觉得是最恰当的
{\fscx80\fscy80}But since you have, I guess you'd better do what you think best.{\r}

853
01:06:34,587 --> 01:06:38,023
我不管你怎样处置哈里 只要你别弄活他就行了
{\fscx80\fscy80}I don't care what you do with Harry, as long as you don't bring him back to life.{\r}

854
01:06:39,692 --> 01:06:43,219
-那我可以放开手做了 -只要你愿意
{\fscx80\fscy80}- I have a free hand, then. - Free as a bird.{\r}

855
01:06:43,296 --> 01:06:45,730
而我知道的就是 那已经成为历史了
{\fscx80\fscy80}As far as I'm concerned, it's ancient history.{\r}

856
01:06:45,798 --> 01:06:47,959
等等，詹尼弗
{\fscx80\fscy80}Wait a minute,Jennifer.{\r}

857
01:06:48,034 --> 01:06:50,366
我想我们忘了什么
{\fscx80\fscy80}I think we've forgotten something.{\r}

858
01:06:50,436 --> 01:06:53,530
你有没考虑过，如果这件事 公之于众，那么你的婚姻…
{\fscx80\fscy80}Do you realize if this thing comes out, that all the details of your marriage...{\r}

859
01:06:53,606 --> 01:06:55,801
不就成了公众事件了？
{\fscx80\fscy80}will be public property?{\r}

860
01:06:57,610 --> 01:07:02,411
-噢 -我得承认，我还真没想到这点
{\fscx80\fscy80}- Oh. - I must confess, I hadn't thought of that, either.{\r}

861
01:07:02,515 --> 01:07:06,144
-你这次把哈里放在哪儿？ -就摆在橡树旁
{\fscx80\fscy80}- Where'd you put Harry this time? - Over by the big oak tree.{\r}

862
01:07:06,219 --> 01:07:08,312
我去拿铁铲
{\fscx80\fscy80}I'll get my shovel.{\r}

863
01:07:08,421 --> 01:07:11,049
恐怕我给你们带来麻烦了
{\fscx80\fscy80}I'm afraid I'm causing you rather a lot of hard work.{\r}

864
01:07:11,124 --> 01:07:13,115
-对不起 -别客气了
{\fscx80\fscy80}I'm sorry. Not at all, not at all.{\r}

865
01:07:13,159 --> 01:07:16,128
噢，我来拿吧
{\fscx80\fscy80}Well, let's all go up there.{\r}

866
01:07:17,530 --> 01:07:20,590
你知道吧 我之前还没出席过葬礼
{\fscx80\fscy80}You know, I've never been to a homemade funeral before.{\r}

867
01:07:20,666 --> 01:07:24,193
我出席过
{\fscx80\fscy80}[Chuckles] I have.{\r}

868
01:07:24,270 --> 01:07:27,000
这是我的第三次
{\fscx80\fscy80}This is my third.{\r}

869
01:07:27,073 --> 01:07:29,405
都集中在一天了
{\fscx80\fscy80}All in one day.{\r}

870
01:07:35,681 --> 01:07:39,139
噢，让我们上土吧
{\fscx80\fscy80}[Sam ] Well, let's get it over with.{\r}

871
01:07:39,185 --> 01:07:41,153
好的
{\fscx80\fscy80}Yes.{\r}

872
01:07:53,199 --> 01:07:55,394
我想我们该拿水泥加固
{\fscx80\fscy80}[Captain] I think we ought to cement it over.{\r}

873
01:07:55,468 --> 01:07:58,926
明年春天，我会种些蓝莓
{\fscx80\fscy80}[Miss Gravely] Next spring I'll set out some blueberry bushes.{\r}

874
01:07:59,005 --> 01:08:01,735
你能不能种点别的？ 丁香什么的？
{\fscx80\fscy80}[Captain] Couldn't you make it something else? Lilacs maybe?{\r}

875
01:08:01,807 --> 01:08:03,775
我想还是顺其自然吧
{\fscx80\fscy80}[Sam] I think nature'll take good care of it.{\r}

876
01:08:03,809 --> 01:08:07,768
-来点祷告吧？ -我想不到有什么好说的
{\fscx80\fscy80}How about a little service? [Sam] I can't think of anything to say.{\r}

877
01:08:07,880 --> 01:08:10,974
-而且我的手臂很疼 -没时间做祷告了
{\fscx80\fscy80}Besides, my arms ache. [Jennifer] It's too late to say prayers.{\r}

878
01:08:11,083 --> 01:08:14,382
而且无论他会去哪儿 他现在就在这儿
{\fscx80\fscy80}Besides, wherever he was going, he's there now.{\r}

879
01:08:14,487 --> 01:08:16,546
再见了，哈里.我会原谅你的
{\fscx80\fscy80}Bye, Harry. I forgive you.{\r}

880
01:08:25,298 --> 01:08:27,698
喇叭在欢迎哈里呢
{\fscx80\fscy80}[Captain] Trumpets welcoming Harry.{\r}

881
01:08:27,800 --> 01:08:31,201
-你也不是太清楚哈里 -我想画你现在的样子，詹尼弗
{\fscx80\fscy80}You didn't know Harry. I'd like to paint you like that,Jennifer.{\r}

882
01:08:31,237 --> 01:08:33,467
在月光的映衬下你非常的美
{\fscx80\fscy80}You look beautiful, glistening in the moonlight.{\r}

883
01:08:35,541 --> 01:08:37,509
听起来像是从村子 那边传过来的
{\fscx80\fscy80}[Captain] Sounds as if it's coming down from near the village.{\r}

884
01:08:37,543 --> 01:08:39,511
我知道是什么
{\fscx80\fscy80}[Miss Gravely] I know what it is.{\r}

885
01:08:39,545 --> 01:08:41,536
那是幻影公共马车的号召…
{\fscx80\fscy80}It's the call of the phantom stagecoach...{\r}

886
01:08:41,614 --> 01:08:46,017
-200年前的每晚都会经过这儿 -幻影公共马车？
{\fscx80\fscy80}that used to pass by here each night 2OO years ago. Phantom coach?{\r}

887
01:08:46,118 --> 01:08:49,315
那条老的收费公路过去 是经过那儿的山丘
{\fscx80\fscy80}The old turnpike used to run across those foothills over there.{\r}

888
01:08:49,422 --> 01:08:52,220
入夜后就好像拦路强盗
{\fscx80\fscy80}[Sam] Oh, to be a highwayman on a night like this.{\r}

889
01:08:52,325 --> 01:08:54,555
听到吗，有人在跑
{\fscx80\fscy80}[Jennifer] Listen. Somebody's running. [ Indistinct Shouting ]{\r}

890
01:08:54,627 --> 01:08:57,357
-马吧？ -如果是马，应该会叫的
{\fscx80\fscy80}Horses? If it's a horse, it's learned how to shout.{\r}

891
01:08:57,430 --> 01:09:00,695
-她在说什么？ -待会我就知道了，她在跑过来
{\fscx80\fscy80}What's she saying? We'll know in a minute. She's coming this way.{\r}

892
01:09:00,766 --> 01:09:05,567
-山姆.马洛！ -我是维格.老维格
{\fscx80\fscy80}Sam Marlow! It's Wiggy. Old Wiggy.{\r}

893
01:09:06,739 --> 01:09:11,733
马洛！马洛！
{\fscx80\fscy80}Mr. Marlow! Mr. Marlow!{\r}

894
01:09:11,844 --> 01:09:15,405
-维格，你来这儿干什么？ 我，他，你要…
{\fscx80\fscy80}Wiggy, what on earth do you want? L... He... You... Wants...{\r}

895
01:09:15,481 --> 01:09:17,676
-顺一下气吧 -他是个百万富翁
{\fscx80\fscy80}Catch your breath. He's a millionaire.{\r}

896
01:09:17,750 --> 01:09:20,878
-谁啊？ -他要买你的画，马洛
{\fscx80\fscy80}Who? He wants to buy your pictures, Mr. Marlow.{\r}

897
01:09:20,953 --> 01:09:23,183
-哪幅画？ -所有或许会更多
{\fscx80\fscy80}Which pictures? All of'em and more besides.{\r}

898
01:09:23,256 --> 01:09:25,520
他说你是个天才
{\fscx80\fscy80}He says you're a genius.{\r}

899
01:09:25,591 --> 01:09:28,856
他说得很对，但他要买了我 所有的画可挺让人难以置信的
{\fscx80\fscy80}He's right, but it's hard to believe he wants to buy all my pictures.{\r}

900
01:09:28,961 --> 01:09:31,521
我也觉得很惊讶 但至少该和他聊聊吧
{\fscx80\fscy80}[Miss Gravely] I'd be too curious to refuse at least to talk to him.{\r}

901
01:09:31,597 --> 01:09:34,088
别错失良机了
{\fscx80\fscy80}[Wiggy] Don't turn down a good chance.{\r}

902
01:09:34,166 --> 01:09:36,600
好的，我去和他谈谈
{\fscx80\fscy80}All right, I'll talk to him.{\r}

903
01:09:38,471 --> 01:09:41,372
-我们在挖檫木根 -檫木茶对你有好处
{\fscx80\fscy80}We're digging sassafras root. [Wiggy] Sassafras tea's mighty good for you.{\r}

904
01:09:41,407 --> 01:09:44,672
维格斯先生说它能在 他死之前治好他的关节炎
{\fscx80\fscy80}Mr. Wiggs always swore it cured his arthritis just before he died.{\r}

905
01:09:44,777 --> 01:09:46,677
那个百万富翁开多少价？
{\fscx80\fscy80}[Captain] How much does the millionaire want to pay?{\r}

906
01:09:46,779 --> 01:09:51,682
那幅看起来像是在雷暴中 很多颜色的画我开价7美元
{\fscx80\fscy80}I asked seven dollars for that one looks like a lot of blobs of color in a thunderstorm.{\r}

907
01:09:51,717 --> 01:09:53,844
-还有呢？-他说没事 而且还说这些可真是无价之宝
{\fscx80\fscy80}[Sam] And? Said he couldn't think of it. Said they were priceless.{\r}

908
01:09:53,919 --> 01:09:57,047
听起来就像是我在幼儿园 画的那样
{\fscx80\fscy80}[Captain] Sounds like something I painted in kindergarten.{\r}

909
01:09:57,123 --> 01:09:59,921
我要你知道 这幅画的涵义是世界的开始
{\fscx80\fscy80}[Sam] I'll have you know that picture's symbolic of the beginning of the world.{\r}

910
01:09:59,992 --> 01:10:03,587
这是也我在幼儿园听到的 关于这世界的说法
{\fscx80\fscy80}[Captain] That's where I first heard of the world, at kindergarten.{\r}

911
01:10:04,130 --> 01:10:08,328
噢，我的朋友是现代 博物馆的美术评论家
{\fscx80\fscy80}Yes, and my friend here, art critic for the Modern Museum...{\r}

912
01:10:08,401 --> 01:10:11,598
恕我无礼 美术评论家说什么可与我无关
{\fscx80\fscy80}Don't think I'm rude, but it doesn't matter to me what an art critic says.{\r}

913
01:10:11,704 --> 01:10:15,140
-就这样吗？ -我知道我的画很棒
{\fscx80\fscy80}Is that so? I know my paintings are good.{\r}

914
01:10:15,207 --> 01:10:18,643
又不是那美术评论家购买 而是你.所以最主要是你怎么想
{\fscx80\fscy80}He doesn't want them; you do. So all that matters is what you think.{\r}

915
01:10:18,711 --> 01:10:22,909
我想这是天才的作品 我所有都买了
{\fscx80\fscy80}I think they are works of genius, and I want to buy them all.{\r}

916
01:10:24,517 --> 01:10:26,917
-太糟糕了  -为什么？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Too bad. Why?{\r}

917
01:10:27,019 --> 01:10:30,648
我在想我决定不卖它们 而且你也买不起
{\fscx80\fscy80}Just decided I can't sell them. Besides, you couldn't afford them.{\r}

918
01:10:30,723 --> 01:10:32,714
噢
{\fscx80\fscy80}Oh.{\r}

919
01:10:32,825 --> 01:10:35,726
噢，钱吧
{\fscx80\fscy80}Uh... Money.{\r}

920
01:10:35,828 --> 01:10:39,764
山姆，别傻了.让他付钱就是
{\fscx80\fscy80}Sammy. Don't be a fool. Make him pay through the nose.{\r}

921
01:10:39,832 --> 01:10:42,824
快啊，马洛先生.现实点
{\fscx80\fscy80}Go ahead, Mr. Marlow. Be reasonable.{\r}

922
01:10:42,935 --> 01:10:44,994
如果你喜欢，过分点也没事
{\fscx80\fscy80}Be unreasonable, if you want.{\r}

923
01:10:45,071 --> 01:10:47,039
你怎么看？
{\fscx80\fscy80}What do you say?{\r}

924
01:10:50,276 --> 01:10:52,767
这是你的作品，你拿主意
{\fscx80\fscy80}It's your genius. It's up to you.{\r}

925
01:10:56,649 --> 01:10:59,948
好的.世界上你最喜欢什么？
{\fscx80\fscy80}All right then. What do you like most in the whole world?{\r}

926
01:11:02,188 --> 01:11:05,351
我也说不清.草莓吧
{\fscx80\fscy80}I don't know. Strawberries, I guess.{\r}

927
01:11:06,392 --> 01:11:08,360
草莓，写下吧
{\fscx80\fscy80}Strawberries. Write that down.{\r}

928
01:11:08,394 --> 01:11:12,160
两盒新鲜草莓，每月一次 无论是什么季节
{\fscx80\fscy80}Two boxes of fresh strawberries, first of each month, in and out of season...{\r}

929
01:11:12,264 --> 01:11:14,164
从现在开始
{\fscx80\fscy80}from now on.{\r}

930
01:11:14,266 --> 01:11:16,666
噢，很简单.还有什么？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Well, it's simple. What else?{\r}

931
01:11:16,702 --> 01:11:18,863
安尼卡喜欢什么？
{\fscx80\fscy80}What would Arnie like?{\r}

932
01:11:20,206 --> 01:11:22,174
化学药品
{\fscx80\fscy80}A chemical set.{\r}

933
01:11:22,208 --> 01:11:25,700
-哪种？  -很难闻那种
{\fscx80\fscy80}What kind? Whatever smells the worst.{\r}

934
01:11:25,778 --> 01:11:28,212
-听到了吗？ -听到了
{\fscx80\fscy80}Got that? Right.{\r}

935
01:11:28,280 --> 01:11:30,874
一种很难闻的化学药品
{\fscx80\fscy80}One smelly chemical set.{\r}

936
01:11:30,983 --> 01:11:33,042
维格，你想要什么？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Wiggy. Wiggy, what would you like?{\r}

937
01:11:33,119 --> 01:11:35,849
收银机，镀铭碟，一个响铃
{\fscx80\fscy80}Cash register. Chromium plated. One that rings a bell.{\r}

938
01:11:35,921 --> 01:11:38,389
-有地方放吗？ -我会找到地方的
{\fscx80\fscy80}Got room for one? I'll find room.{\r}

939
01:11:38,491 --> 01:11:41,221
-收银机 -镀铭碟，还有一个响铃？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Cash register. Chromium plated. One that rings a bell?{\r}

940
01:11:41,293 --> 01:11:43,227
知道
{\fscx80\fscy80}Check.{\r}

941
01:11:43,295 --> 01:11:46,287
格勒夫利小姐 来一个装修漂亮的客厅怎样？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Miss Gravely, a beauty parlor, fully equipped?{\r}

942
01:11:46,332 --> 01:11:48,562
有什么用？
{\fscx80\fscy80}What for?{\r}

943
01:11:48,634 --> 01:11:53,333
我要一个有很多礼物的嫁妆箱
{\fscx80\fscy80}A hope chest... filled with the things I should have put in it and didn't.{\r}

944
01:11:53,406 --> 01:11:57,069
一个嫁妆箱，要有很多嫁妆
{\fscx80\fscy80}A hope chest, full of hope.{\r}

945
01:11:57,143 --> 01:11:59,475
船长呢？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Captain?{\r}

946
01:11:59,545 --> 01:12:02,776
一只上乘猎枪，火药
{\fscx80\fscy80}A good shotgun, plenty of ammunition,{\r}

947
01:12:02,848 --> 01:12:08,150
一些灯芯绒裤子，一件白衬衣 和一顶打猎帽，要褐色的
{\fscx80\fscy80}some corduroy britches, a plain shirt and a hunting cap, a brown one.{\r}

948
01:12:09,455 --> 01:12:11,719
戴维.克罗斯基…这些作品
{\fscx80\fscy80}Davy Crockett... the works.{\r}

949
01:12:11,824 --> 01:12:15,419
好了，就这样.我想 这些画就是你的了
{\fscx80\fscy80}Well, that's it, I guess. The paintings are yours.{\r}

950
01:12:15,528 --> 01:12:17,428
还有你的呢？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Yes, but what about you?{\r}

951
01:12:17,530 --> 01:12:20,055
对啊，山姆，你也要点什么吧
{\fscx80\fscy80}Yes, Sam, you've gotta ask for something.{\r}

952
01:12:20,132 --> 01:12:22,066
好的，我想想
{\fscx80\fscy80}Well, let's see.{\r}

953
01:12:25,438 --> 01:12:28,271
就这样
{\fscx80\fscy80}That's it.{\r}

954
01:12:28,340 --> 01:12:30,968
-什么？ -不好意思
{\fscx80\fscy80}- What's it? - Pardon me.{\r}

955
01:12:35,948 --> 01:12:37,848
你看怎样？
{\fscx80\fscy80}What do you think?{\r}

956
01:12:40,553 --> 01:12:43,613
好的，我想挺好安排的
{\fscx80\fscy80}Yes, I think that can be easily arranged.{\r}

957
01:12:46,559 --> 01:12:48,686
好的，就这样吧
{\fscx80\fscy80}Well. That's it, then.{\r}

958
01:12:48,761 --> 01:12:51,753
我早上来取画吧
{\fscx80\fscy80}I'll come back in the morning for all these paintings.{\r}

959
01:12:51,797 --> 01:12:54,766
马洛先生，我会记住
{\fscx80\fscy80}Mr. Marlow, this has been a night...{\r}

960
01:12:54,800 --> 01:12:57,030
今天晚上的
{\fscx80\fscy80}that I shall remember the rest of my life.{\r}

961
01:12:57,102 --> 01:13:00,196
欢迎再来 下个月会有更多的画
{\fscx80\fscy80}Come back again. Have some more paintings for you next month.{\r}

962
01:13:00,272 --> 01:13:03,366
即使你提价
{\fscx80\fscy80}And you'll have a steady customer in me,{\r}

963
01:13:03,476 --> 01:13:06,036
我也是你固定的顾客
{\fscx80\fscy80}even if you raise your prices.{\r}

964
01:13:06,111 --> 01:13:08,170
好了，再见
{\fscx80\fscy80}Well, good night, everyone.{\r}

965
01:13:08,280 --> 01:13:10,180
-再见 -再见
{\fscx80\fscy80}Good night. Good night.{\r}

966
01:13:10,282 --> 01:13:12,307
谢谢，年轻人
{\fscx80\fscy80}All right, young man. [Millionaire Clears Throat]{\r}

967
01:13:17,223 --> 01:13:19,555
恭喜你，山姆.干得好
{\fscx80\fscy80}[Captain ] Congratulations, Sammy. Good boy.{\r}

968
01:13:19,625 --> 01:13:23,356
-我做得对吗？ -你做得很对，山姆
{\fscx80\fscy80}Did I do the right thing? You did just the right thing, Sam.{\r}

969
01:13:23,429 --> 01:13:26,694
好的
{\fscx80\fscy80}Good.{\r}

970
01:13:26,799 --> 01:13:29,290
因为你这样想对我来说很重要
{\fscx80\fscy80}Because it's important to me that you think so.{\r}

971
01:13:29,401 --> 01:13:31,301
为什么？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Why?{\r}

972
01:13:31,403 --> 01:13:33,803
因为我爱你，我要娶你
{\fscx80\fscy80}Because I love you. I want to marry you.{\r}

973
01:13:36,008 --> 01:13:37,999
噢！
{\fscx80\fscy80}Oh! [Chuckling]{\r}

974
01:13:41,714 --> 01:13:44,410
-你要娶我？   -嗯，对啊
{\fscx80\fscy80}You want to marry me? Um-hmm. Why not?{\r}

975
01:13:46,852 --> 01:13:49,821
我今天才刚刚得到自由
{\fscx80\fscy80}Because... Because I just got my freedom today.{\r}

976
01:13:49,922 --> 01:13:52,390
来得容易，去得快
{\fscx80\fscy80}Easy come, easy go.{\r}

977
01:13:52,458 --> 01:13:55,325
而且如果你嫁给我 你还可以保留你的自由啊
{\fscx80\fscy80}Besides, if you married me, you'd keep your freedom.{\r}

978
01:13:57,630 --> 01:14:00,155
你真是独一无二
{\fscx80\fscy80}You must be practically unique, then.{\r}

979
01:14:00,232 --> 01:14:04,362
我尊敬自由而且我爱自由
{\fscx80\fscy80}I respect freedom. More than that, I love freedom.{\r}

980
01:14:04,436 --> 01:14:07,530
我们会是世界上最自由的夫妻
{\fscx80\fscy80}We might be the only free married couple in the world.{\r}

981
01:14:11,377 --> 01:14:13,845
太突然了，山姆
{\fscx80\fscy80}This is very sudden, Sam.{\r}

982
01:14:18,050 --> 01:14:20,848
你得给点时间我考虑考虑
{\fscx80\fscy80}You'll have to give me a little time to think about it.{\r}

983
01:14:20,953 --> 01:14:24,855
好的，我们回到你家 你就得决定了
{\fscx80\fscy80}Only fair. I'll give you until we get back to your house.{\r}

984
01:14:31,297 --> 01:14:34,824
-今晚这儿怎么了？ 有喜事
{\fscx80\fscy80}- What's goin' on here this time of night? - The most wonderful thing.{\r}

985
01:14:34,900 --> 01:14:37,494
马洛先生把他的全部画 都买给了一位百万富翁
{\fscx80\fscy80}Mr. Marlow sold all his paintings to a millionaire.{\r}

986
01:14:37,570 --> 01:14:40,061
-得到了很多    -钱吗？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Got more'n I ever figured he'd get. Money?{\r}

987
01:14:40,172 --> 01:14:43,630
不完全是钱
{\fscx80\fscy80}Well, not exactly money.{\r}

988
01:14:43,709 --> 01:14:46,610
我知道这些东西不该占地方
{\fscx80\fscy80}I always knew they weren't worth the space.{\r}

989
01:14:46,679 --> 01:14:50,012
我在一个闲逛的流浪汉 身上找到了这个
{\fscx80\fscy80}I found these on a tramp hangin' 'round here.{\r}

990
01:14:50,082 --> 01:14:53,415
他说他在一个死尸上找到的
{\fscx80\fscy80}Said he found 'em. On a... dead man.{\r}

991
01:14:55,220 --> 01:14:57,415
就带我去了他所说的地方
{\fscx80\fscy80}Took me to where he said he found him, and...{\r}

992
01:14:58,724 --> 01:15:00,692
我可没看到什么死尸
{\fscx80\fscy80}I didn't see any body.{\r}

993
01:15:03,796 --> 01:15:06,856
蒙彼利埃，2000
{\fscx80\fscy80}Montpelier 2000.{\r}

994
01:15:06,932 --> 01:15:09,696
-这是州际警察的电话-嗯
{\fscx80\fscy80}[ Wiggy ] That's the state police number. Uh-huh.{\r}

995
01:15:09,802 --> 01:15:12,828
我想我们还是回去吧
{\fscx80\fscy80}I think, uh, we'd better get going.{\r}

996
01:15:12,905 --> 01:15:15,430
谢谢你给的收银机，马洛先生
{\fscx80\fscy80}Thank you, Mr. Marlow, for the cash register.{\r}

997
01:15:15,507 --> 01:15:17,441
别客气.晚安
{\fscx80\fscy80}It was a pleasure. Good night.{\r}

998
01:15:17,509 --> 01:15:19,670
-晚安  -晚安
{\fscx80\fscy80}Good night. Good night. Good night.{\r}

999
01:15:19,745 --> 01:15:21,713
晚安
{\fscx80\fscy80}Good night.{\r}

1000
01:15:21,747 --> 01:15:23,715
-晚安    -晚安，船长
{\fscx80\fscy80}Good night. Good night, Captain.{\r}

1001
01:15:26,518 --> 01:15:30,113
我是代理州长加尔文.维格斯
{\fscx80\fscy80}[ Door Closes ] This is Deputy Sheriff Calvin Wiggs.{\r}

1002
01:15:30,222 --> 01:15:32,122
好的，我等一下
{\fscx80\fscy80}Yeah, I'll wait.{\r}

1003
01:15:49,041 --> 01:15:52,135
妈妈？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Ma?{\r}

1004
01:15:52,244 --> 01:15:56,078
-什么事？ -地上有幅画
{\fscx80\fscy80}- Yes? - This picture here on the floor.{\r}

1005
01:15:56,148 --> 01:16:00,175
这是新画.他今天画的 但不会出售
{\fscx80\fscy80}It's a new one. He did it today, but it isn't for sale.{\r}

1006
01:16:00,252 --> 01:16:03,346
-为什么？ -你得问问他
{\fscx80\fscy80}Why not? You'll have to ask him that.{\r}

1007
01:16:03,455 --> 01:16:07,050
他去詹尼弗.罗杰斯的家时 就放在这儿了
{\fscx80\fscy80}He left it on his way over to Jennifer Rogers' house.{\r}

1008
01:16:07,159 --> 01:16:10,060
我猜他忘了拿回家
{\fscx80\fscy80}Guess he didn't have time to take it home.{\r}

1009
01:16:12,164 --> 01:16:14,598
你突然对艺术感兴趣了？
{\fscx80\fscy80}You suddenly got interested in art?{\r}

1010
01:16:15,768 --> 01:16:18,532
不是
{\fscx80\fscy80}No.{\r}

1011
01:16:18,604 --> 01:16:21,869
这和一个…
{\fscx80\fscy80}It's just that it matches the description of...{\r}

1012
01:16:21,974 --> 01:16:24,670
噢，你好，船长
{\fscx80\fscy80}Oh, hello, Sergeant.{\r}

1013
01:16:24,777 --> 01:16:26,677
加尔文.维格斯
{\fscx80\fscy80}Calvin Wiggs.{\r}

1014
01:16:26,779 --> 01:16:29,407
这里有件事你或许感兴趣的
{\fscx80\fscy80}Got something that might interest you a little.{\r}

1015
01:16:29,481 --> 01:16:33,577
我拿到了一双流浪汉 偷回来的鞋子
{\fscx80\fscy80}It seems I picked up this tramp with a pair of stolen shoes...{\r}

1016
01:16:33,686 --> 01:16:36,120
还有一个很离奇的死尸故事
{\fscx80\fscy80}and a wild story about a corpse.{\r}

1017
01:16:56,842 --> 01:16:59,936
你怎么看？他拿着哈里.沃普 的鞋子走进来
{\fscx80\fscy80}What do you think? Him walking in with Harry Worp's shoes...{\r}

1018
01:17:00,012 --> 01:17:03,140
并给警察电话
{\fscx80\fscy80}in his hand and then that phone call to the police.{\r}

1019
01:17:03,215 --> 01:17:05,706
我也不是很清楚.或许是我错了
{\fscx80\fscy80}Don't know. I may be wrong,{\r}

1020
01:17:05,818 --> 01:17:07,843
但我想他不会想到我们
{\fscx80\fscy80}but I don't think he's tied us into it yet.{\r}

1021
01:17:07,920 --> 01:17:10,218
噢，他看我的眼神
{\fscx80\fscy80}Oh, the way he looked at me.{\r}

1022
01:17:10,322 --> 01:17:12,756
如果他知道了 他就会不让我们走了
{\fscx80\fscy80}If he'd known anything, he'd have kept us there.{\r}

1023
01:17:12,825 --> 01:17:17,387
但现代警察的办案方法是攻心 山姆，攻心计
{\fscx80\fscy80}But modern police methods are all psychological now, Sammy. Psychological.{\r}

1024
01:17:17,463 --> 01:17:22,264
他们会不停地磨到你身心俱惫
{\fscx80\fscy80}They just wear you down and wear you down until...{\r}

1025
01:17:22,334 --> 01:17:25,326
然后你就欣然进入毒气室
{\fscx80\fscy80}you're almost grateful to get into that gas chamber.{\r}

1026
01:17:26,872 --> 01:17:31,741
警察可能会告诉他，如果 这鞋子大小一样的话，就看着他们
{\fscx80\fscy80}The police'll probably tell him, if the shoes fit, to keep them.{\r}

1027
01:17:31,777 --> 01:17:34,371
噢，好的
{\fscx80\fscy80}Oh, well.{\r}

1028
01:17:44,356 --> 01:17:47,621
-我已经决定了，山姆   -
{\fscx80\fscy80}I've decided, Sam. Decided what?{\r}

1029
01:17:47,693 --> 01:17:49,661
我愿意嫁给你
{\fscx80\fscy80}I will marry you,{\r}

1030
01:17:49,695 --> 01:17:52,163
如果你还记得你刚向 我求过婚的话
{\fscx80\fscy80}if you haven't forgotten about asking me.{\r}

1031
01:17:54,199 --> 01:17:57,396
我非常喜欢你
{\fscx80\fscy80}I'm... I'm very fond of you and,{\r}

1032
01:17:57,469 --> 01:17:59,869
还有你会做安尼卡的好父亲的
{\fscx80\fscy80}I think you'd make a good father for Arnie...{\r}

1033
01:18:01,607 --> 01:18:05,976
其它原因就先别说了
{\fscx80\fscy80}and for some other reasons best left unsaid.{\r}

1034
01:18:07,279 --> 01:18:09,247
用结婚来过冬是个舒适的方法
{\fscx80\fscy80}Marriage is the comfortable way to spend the winter,{\r}

1035
01:18:09,314 --> 01:18:13,307
但现在最好想出一个合理的 故事来骗过警察
{\fscx80\fscy80}but right now we should be working on some good story to satisfy the state police...{\r}

1036
01:18:13,385 --> 01:18:16,320
以防万一他们出现
{\fscx80\fscy80}if they should turn up.{\r}

1037
01:18:16,388 --> 01:18:20,484
你知道吗？我可差点忘了
{\fscx80\fscy80}Would you believe it? I'd almost forgotten that proposal.{\r}

1038
01:18:20,592 --> 01:18:24,119
-我可是有证人的，山姆 -噢，我现在记得了
{\fscx80\fscy80}I have witnesses, Sam. Oh, I remember now.{\r}

1039
01:18:24,196 --> 01:18:28,155
好的，你有了一位丈夫
{\fscx80\fscy80}All right, you've got yourself a husband.{\r}

1040
01:18:28,233 --> 01:18:30,428
我现在吻你以表真心
{\fscx80\fscy80}I think I'll kiss you now to prove it.{\r}

1041
01:18:38,210 --> 01:18:42,044
轻点，山姆.我有点紧张
{\fscx80\fscy80}Lightly, Sam. I have a very short fuse.{\r}

1042
01:18:51,523 --> 01:18:54,083
多美的一幕啊
{\fscx80\fscy80}What a pretty sight.{\r}

1043
01:19:01,066 --> 01:19:04,866
山姆 你让百万富翁帮你干什么？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Sam, what did you ask the millionaire for?{\r}

1044
01:19:11,777 --> 01:19:13,745
那样非常实在
{\fscx80\fscy80}That's very practical.{\r}

1045
01:19:18,150 --> 01:19:20,482
恭喜你，亲爱的
{\fscx80\fscy80}Congratulations, my dear.{\r}

1046
01:19:20,552 --> 01:19:23,988
你是个幸运的人，山姆 我想你们会幸福的
{\fscx80\fscy80}You're a lucky man, Sammy. I think you'll both be very happy.{\r}

1047
01:19:24,056 --> 01:19:25,990
-谢谢 -如果在埋哈里过程中
{\fscx80\fscy80}Thank you. If I grumbled too much...{\r}

1048
01:19:26,058 --> 01:19:29,721
发了太多牢骚 那就不好意思了
{\fscx80\fscy80}at my share of the work in burying Harry, I'm sorry.{\r}

1049
01:19:29,795 --> 01:19:31,922
现在看来是值得的
{\fscx80\fscy80}I can see now it was well worth it.{\r}

1050
01:19:31,997 --> 01:19:35,797
-如果我还能帮上什么 -等等，等等
{\fscx80\fscy80}And if I can do anything else... Hold it, hold it, hold it.{\r}

1051
01:19:39,504 --> 01:19:43,964
-怎么了，山姆？ -哈里，我们还没解决他
{\fscx80\fscy80}- What's wrong, Sam? - Harry. We're not quite finished with him yet.{\r}

1052
01:19:44,076 --> 01:19:47,807
山姆，算了吧 都已经埋了他三遍
{\fscx80\fscy80}Sam, if anybody's through, it's Harry. He's been buried three times.{\r}

1053
01:19:47,880 --> 01:19:50,280
在我们结婚之前 你得证明你真的得到自由了
{\fscx80\fscy80}Before we can get married, you're gonna have to prove that you're free.{\r}

1054
01:19:50,382 --> 01:19:54,341
-要证明你的自由 你就得怎么哈里… -死了
{\fscx80\fscy80}To prove you're free, you'll have to prove that Harry... Is dead.{\r}

1055
01:19:55,787 --> 01:20:00,815
-真是太复杂了 -噢！
{\fscx80\fscy80}- What a horrible complication. - Oh!{\r}

1056
01:20:00,893 --> 01:20:04,158
我不知道怎样
{\fscx80\fscy80}I don't know that it is.{\r}

1057
01:20:04,229 --> 01:20:06,493
你看我干什么啊？
{\fscx80\fscy80}What are you looking at me for?{\r}

1058
01:20:09,601 --> 01:20:12,263
山姆，我可以帮你做任何事 但拜托…
{\fscx80\fscy80}Sammy, I'll do anything to help you, but please,{\r}

1059
01:20:12,337 --> 01:20:15,101
拜托你别叫我再挖他了！
{\fscx80\fscy80}please don't ask me to dig up Harry again!{\r}

1060
01:20:15,207 --> 01:20:18,506
-噢，去吧，船长 -不，我们不能这样
{\fscx80\fscy80}- Oh, come, come now, Captain. - No, we can't.{\r}

1061
01:20:18,610 --> 01:20:21,511
-莫非你担心不良的传言… -不，我不会
{\fscx80\fscy80}If you're thinking of the bad publicity... NO, I'm nOt.{\r}

1062
01:20:22,915 --> 01:20:26,749
我觉得山姆能体谅一切
{\fscx80\fscy80}I think Sam would be worth just about anything.{\r}

1063
01:20:26,818 --> 01:20:29,218
我倒是为你想，格勒夫利小姐
{\fscx80\fscy80}I'm thinking of you, Miss Gravely.{\r}

1064
01:20:29,321 --> 01:20:34,349
谋杀就是谋杀了 无论当时情况是多么的糟糕
{\fscx80\fscy80}Murder is murder, no matter how exonerating the circumstances and...{\r}

1065
01:20:34,426 --> 01:20:36,724
对你来说一点好处都没有
{\fscx80\fscy80}It just wouldn't look nice at all for you.{\r}

1066
01:20:36,828 --> 01:20:39,729
对！最好就这么让他待着
{\fscx80\fscy80}That's right! Better let him stay where he is.{\r}

1067
01:20:39,765 --> 01:20:43,633
你就不必等7年来判定一个人 是否死了
{\fscx80\fscy80}You won't have to wait seven years to presume death, anyway.{\r}

1068
01:20:43,669 --> 01:20:45,637
7年！我都老掉牙了
{\fscx80\fscy80}Seven years! I'll be an old man.{\r}

1069
01:20:45,671 --> 01:20:48,731
别傻了.你已经不止等7年了
{\fscx80\fscy80}Don't be silly. You waited far longer than seven years already.{\r}

1070
01:20:48,840 --> 01:20:52,139
对，但现在你知道我在等什么吗
{\fscx80\fscy80}Yes, but now I know what I'm waiting for.{\r}

1071
01:20:52,244 --> 01:20:54,371
我坚持要挖起那个可怜的人
{\fscx80\fscy80}I insist that you dig the wretched man up.{\r}

1072
01:20:54,446 --> 01:20:57,074
我才不管他们说什么
{\fscx80\fscy80}I don't care a hoot what they say.{\r}

1073
01:20:57,149 --> 01:21:00,312
他们认识我就会意识到 这个人肯定是疯的
{\fscx80\fscy80}They'd only have to know me to realize the man must have been mad.{\r}

1074
01:21:00,385 --> 01:21:04,788
-我不同意 -噢，怀尔斯船长
{\fscx80\fscy80}I disagree! Huh! Really, Capt. Wiles.{\r}

1075
01:21:06,558 --> 01:21:08,651
好的
{\fscx80\fscy80}Well...{\r}

1076
01:21:08,760 --> 01:21:10,921
我去挖他吧
{\fscx80\fscy80}I'll dig him up.{\r}

1077
01:21:10,996 --> 01:21:13,396
我们最好在加尔文.维格斯 叫那些州际警察到这儿前
{\fscx80\fscy80}But we'd better get it done before Calvin Wiggs...{\r}

1078
01:21:13,465 --> 01:21:16,127
把它办妥
{\fscx80\fscy80}gets the state police snooping around here.{\r}

1079
01:21:22,975 --> 01:21:25,705
我在想
{\fscx80\fscy80}[Jennifer] I've been thinking.{\r}

1080
01:21:25,777 --> 01:21:29,941
我在想或许我们可以忘记 这件事是怎样发生的
{\fscx80\fscy80}I've been thinking maybe we could forget the way it really happened.{\r}

1081
01:21:30,015 --> 01:21:32,984
我可以对别人说哈里如何来见我 然后有非常气愤地离开了
{\fscx80\fscy80}I could tell how Harry visited me and went off in such a rage today,{\r}

1082
01:21:33,018 --> 01:21:36,579
而我们只要知道他在这儿就是了
{\fscx80\fscy80}and that's all we'd need to know about his being there.{\r}

1083
01:21:36,688 --> 01:21:38,713
不行，那有人会受到谴责
{\fscx80\fscy80}No, somebody else might get the blame.{\r}

1084
01:21:38,790 --> 01:21:42,851
他们没有比我更好的理由了
{\fscx80\fscy80}And somebody else might not have such a good reason as I did.{\r}

1085
01:21:42,928 --> 01:21:46,295
“有人”是什么意思？
{\fscx80\fscy80}What do you mean "somebody else"?{\r}

1086
01:21:46,398 --> 01:21:50,334
我可以说起码有两个人 有杀哈里的动机
{\fscx80\fscy80}I can think of at least two people with a good reason for having killed Harry.{\r}

1087
01:21:50,402 --> 01:21:54,566
第一个是你，因为你嫁给了 他.然后就是山姆
{\fscx80\fscy80}First you, because you married him. And now Sam.{\r}

1088
01:21:54,639 --> 01:21:58,006
我？我为什么要杀他？ 我可从未见过他
{\fscx80\fscy80}Me? Why would I want to kill him? I never met him before.{\r}

1089
01:21:58,110 --> 01:22:00,578
但你还是有杀他的动机
{\fscx80\fscy80}You could still have a reason for killing him.{\r}

1090
01:22:00,645 --> 01:22:02,772
-她是指我   -对
{\fscx80\fscy80}She means me. Yes.{\r}

1091
01:22:02,848 --> 01:22:06,340
哈里死之后我才爱上詹尼弗的
{\fscx80\fscy80}I didn't fall in love with Jennifer until after Harry was dead.{\r}

1092
01:22:06,418 --> 01:22:08,477
把这个说给警察听吧
{\fscx80\fscy80}Try telling that to the police.{\r}

1093
01:22:08,553 --> 01:22:11,818
她说得对，山姆
{\fscx80\fscy80}She's right, Sammy boy.{\r}

1094
01:22:11,923 --> 01:22:16,451
再想想 我们现在还是面对现实吧
{\fscx80\fscy80}Well, on second thought, we'd better stick to the truth, what there is of it.{\r}

1095
01:22:22,768 --> 01:22:26,898
我们得想想为什么之前 没通知警察
{\fscx80\fscy80}We'll have to think up a reason why the police weren't informed before now.{\r}

1096
01:22:26,972 --> 01:22:30,430
对，他现在就是这样 要费点喉舌解释
{\fscx80\fscy80}Yes, then there's the condition he's in. That'll take some explaining.{\r}

1097
01:22:30,542 --> 01:22:33,136
我们把他清洗一下吧
{\fscx80\fscy80}We'll just clean him up a bit.{\r}

1098
01:22:33,245 --> 01:22:36,043
太可怕了，但我们别无选择
{\fscx80\fscy80}It's horrible, but there's nothing else we can do.{\r}

1099
01:22:36,148 --> 01:22:38,708
我们不能把格勒夫利的 证供复杂化
{\fscx80\fscy80}We can't risk complicating Miss Gravely's confession.{\r}

1100
01:22:38,784 --> 01:22:41,617
至于为什么会延迟了 我可以解释说我非常的难过
{\fscx80\fscy80}And as for the delay, I can explain that I was so upset...{\r}

1101
01:22:41,686 --> 01:22:45,281
-现在我还是回家休息去吧
{\fscx80\fscy80}by the occurrence that... I went straight home and rested.{\r}

1102
01:22:45,357 --> 01:22:49,020
-合情理 -他们会想你也休息得太久了吧
{\fscx80\fscy80}Only natural. They'll think you rested rather a long time.{\r}

1103
01:22:49,094 --> 01:22:52,188
山姆，我可花整晚时间在这儿吵
{\fscx80\fscy80}Sam, I'd rather not spend the whole night debating.{\r}

1104
01:22:52,264 --> 01:22:54,596
我们抬哈里到什么地方 然后清洁他一下吧
{\fscx80\fscy80}Let's get Harry someplace and clean him up.{\r}

1105
01:22:54,666 --> 01:22:59,069
我们离开这儿吧
{\fscx80\fscy80}[Man Talking ] [Captain ] Let's get out of here.{\r}

1106
01:23:09,915 --> 01:23:13,476
爱永远不会去改变真理
{\fscx80\fscy80}Love alters not with his brief hours and weeks.{\r}

1107
01:23:13,585 --> 01:23:16,418
忍受吧，直到天荒地老
{\fscx80\fscy80}Bears it out even to the edge of doom.{\r}

1108
01:23:16,488 --> 01:23:20,390
如果这是错误的 而且需要我来证明
{\fscx80\fscy80}If this be error and upon me proved,{\r}

1109
01:23:20,492 --> 01:23:24,588
我永远都不会 没人会得到爱
{\fscx80\fscy80}I never writ, nor man ever loved.{\r}

1110
01:23:34,306 --> 01:23:38,606
我，我想他遇到了意外 格林保医生
{\fscx80\fscy80}I, uh, I think he met with a bit of an accident, Dr. Greenbow.{\r}

1111
01:23:38,643 --> 01:23:40,611
他的确是
{\fscx80\fscy80}He certainly did.{\r}

1112
01:23:42,314 --> 01:23:44,248
你们哪个发现他的？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Which of you found him?{\r}

1113
01:23:44,316 --> 01:23:47,308
-噢 -他是我的丈夫，医生
{\fscx80\fscy80}Well... He was my husband, Doctor.{\r}

1114
01:23:47,352 --> 01:23:51,015
噢，罗杰斯夫人 我不知道你还有个丈夫
{\fscx80\fscy80}Oh, Mrs. Rogers. I didn't know you had a husband.{\r}

1115
01:23:51,123 --> 01:23:53,387
真不好意思
{\fscx80\fscy80}I'm awfully sorry.{\r}

1116
01:23:53,458 --> 01:23:56,621
没事，医生 我想这就是人生吧
{\fscx80\fscy80}It's all right, Doctor. It's just life, I guess.{\r}

1117
01:23:56,728 --> 01:23:59,288
-他怎么了？  -噢，他….
{\fscx80\fscy80}What happened to him? Well, he...{\r}

1118
01:23:59,364 --> 01:24:04,233
这也是我们想知道的 你能告诉我们是他的死因吗？
{\fscx80\fscy80}That's what we'd like to know. Could you tell us what caused his death? It was so sudden.{\r}

1119
01:24:04,336 --> 01:24:06,827
这方面 我的意见可不是太专业
{\fscx80\fscy80}In this light, my opinion would be little more than a guess.{\r}

1120
01:24:06,938 --> 01:24:09,771
这样，我们还是把他抬到 一个适当的地方吧
{\fscx80\fscy80}In that case, we could take him someplace where you could see better.{\r}

1121
01:24:09,841 --> 01:24:13,436
好的，但我得去拿我的书包 我们在哪儿见？
{\fscx80\fscy80}All right, but I need my bag. Where shall we meet?{\r}

1122
01:24:13,545 --> 01:24:15,945
我带哈里回我的家
{\fscx80\fscy80}I'll take Harry home to my house.{\r}

1123
01:24:19,351 --> 01:24:22,809
最后一次回家了
{\fscx80\fscy80}Going home for the last time.{\r}

1124
01:24:27,492 --> 01:24:29,722
最好是最后一次
{\fscx80\fscy80}Better be the last time.{\r}

1125
01:24:29,794 --> 01:24:33,252
来吧，山姆.我还得帮上一回
{\fscx80\fscy80}Come on, Sam. I've got about one more trip left in me.{\r}

1126
01:24:33,298 --> 01:24:35,493
我帮你拿外衣
{\fscx80\fscy80}I'll get your coats.{\r}

1127
01:25:30,255 --> 01:25:32,223
我来别上吊裤带
{\fscx80\fscy80}I'll get the suspenders on.{\r}

1128
01:25:39,231 --> 01:25:42,632
我不能等了.我得烫干它
{\fscx80\fscy80}I can't wait for this to be ready. I'll have to iron it dry.{\r}

1129
01:25:44,469 --> 01:25:46,437
是不是有点怪怪的
{\fscx80\fscy80}Isn't it odd?{\r}

1130
01:25:46,471 --> 01:25:51,204
这么久的拒绝后 我最终还是得为哈里做家务了
{\fscx80\fscy80}After refusing for so long, here I am finally doing Harry's laundry.{\r}

1131
01:26:09,461 --> 01:26:12,191
噢！
{\fscx80\fscy80}Ah!{\r}

1132
01:26:12,264 --> 01:26:14,323
看
{\fscx80\fscy80}[Whispers] Look.{\r}

1133
01:26:14,399 --> 01:26:16,993
没有什么好大惊小怪的，船长
{\fscx80\fscy80}It's nothing to get excited about, Captain.{\r}

1134
01:26:17,068 --> 01:26:20,060
只是一扇衣柜门
{\fscx80\fscy80}It's only a closet door.{\r}

1135
01:26:20,105 --> 01:26:22,801
噢，我以为是哈里呢
{\fscx80\fscy80}Oh. I thought it was Harry.{\r}

1136
01:26:22,874 --> 01:26:25,604
放松点，船长 没什么好担心的
{\fscx80\fscy80}Relax, Captain. Nothing to worry about.{\r}

1137
01:26:31,383 --> 01:26:34,648
我用高跟鞋砸他的头 留下的伤口怎样？
{\fscx80\fscy80}What about the cut I made on his head with my hiking shoe?{\r}

1138
01:26:34,719 --> 01:26:37,813
噢，我贴上了胶布
{\fscx80\fscy80}[Jennifer] Hmm. I'll put some adhesive tape on it.{\r}

1139
01:26:37,889 --> 01:26:39,880
他们会以为是他死之前 弄伤的
{\fscx80\fscy80}They'll think it was done before he died.{\r}

1140
01:26:39,991 --> 01:26:42,892
这件衬衣烫完后，就可以了
{\fscx80\fscy80}After the shirt's finished, it should be just about everything.{\r}

1141
01:26:44,996 --> 01:26:47,760
-会是谁啊 -我想是加尔文.维格斯的车
{\fscx80\fscy80}If that who I think it is... Calvin Wiggs' car.{\r}

1142
01:27:11,256 --> 01:27:13,417
等等
{\fscx80\fscy80}[Jennifer ] Just one second.{\r}

1143
01:27:23,134 --> 01:27:25,864
噢，加尔文.维格斯 真意外啊
{\fscx80\fscy80}Well, Calvin Wiggs. What a surprise.{\r}

1144
01:27:25,937 --> 01:27:28,838
-山姆在这儿吗？ -在，在，在.他在这儿
{\fscx80\fscy80}Sam here? Yes, yes, yes, he's here.{\r}

1145
01:27:28,873 --> 01:27:31,865
我能见他吗？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Can I see him a minute?{\r}

1146
01:27:31,943 --> 01:27:33,877
-山姆！  -噢？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Sam! Yeah?{\r}

1147
01:27:33,945 --> 01:27:36,277
加尔文.维格斯要见你
{\fscx80\fscy80}Calvin Wiggs is here to see you.{\r}

1148
01:27:36,348 --> 01:27:38,282
告诉他我就出来
{\fscx80\fscy80}Tell him I'll be right out.{\r}

1149
01:27:38,350 --> 01:27:41,842
-他说他就出来 -我怎么不能进去？
{\fscx80\fscy80}He says he'll be right out. Why don't I just go on in?{\r}

1150
01:27:47,492 --> 01:27:49,460
晚上好，加尔文
{\fscx80\fscy80}Evening, Calvin.{\r}

1151
01:27:49,561 --> 01:27:52,962
晚上好，怀尔斯船长 格勒夫利小姐
{\fscx80\fscy80}Evening, Capt. Wiles. Miss Gravely.{\r}

1152
01:27:52,997 --> 01:27:55,124
我们在玩扑克
{\fscx80\fscy80}We've got 'em on the run in four spades.{\r}

1153
01:27:55,200 --> 01:27:58,363
他们应该有方块
{\fscx80\fscy80}[Chuckling] They should have been in diamonds.{\r}

1154
01:27:58,470 --> 01:28:01,303
-玩桥牌吗？ -从来都不沾
{\fscx80\fscy80}Play much bridge? Never play it.{\r}

1155
01:28:01,373 --> 01:28:05,275
-我想也是 -有什么事吗，加尔文？
{\fscx80\fscy80}- That's what I thought. - Something you wanted, Calvin?{\r}

1156
01:28:05,377 --> 01:28:08,710
-你今天去哪儿了，山姆？ 照常工作
{\fscx80\fscy80}- Where were you today, Sam? - Working, as usual.{\r}

1157
01:28:08,780 --> 01:28:12,944
到了曼斯费尔德草地去了吗？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Somewheres down by Mansfield Meadows?{\r}

1158
01:28:13,017 --> 01:28:15,349
或许，我周围去素描.怎么了？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Possibly. I do quite a bit of sketching around. Why?{\r}

1159
01:28:18,890 --> 01:28:21,290
就是在那儿
{\fscx80\fscy80}Is that where, uh...{\r}

1160
01:28:23,228 --> 01:28:25,696
画了这个的吗？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Where you painted this?{\r}

1161
01:28:28,032 --> 01:28:30,398
我把这幅人物肖像 留给你的母亲
{\fscx80\fscy80}I left that portrait with your mother.{\r}

1162
01:28:30,502 --> 01:28:32,902
你怎么拿着它到处走啊？ 会弄坏的
{\fscx80\fscy80}What right do you have to carry it around with you? It might be damaged.{\r}

1163
01:28:33,004 --> 01:28:36,997
噢，可是无价的 山姆会丢了笔买卖
{\fscx80\fscy80}Huh. It could be priceless, and Sam would lose a sale.{\r}

1164
01:28:37,108 --> 01:28:40,737
噢，我会每个月送他盒蓝莓的
{\fscx80\fscy80}Oh, I'll send him a box of blueberries the first of every month.{\r}

1165
01:28:40,812 --> 01:28:43,838
山姆，我想知道的是他在什么 地方画的还有他是谁？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Sam, what I wanna know is where'd you paint it and who is it?{\r}

1166
01:28:43,915 --> 01:28:47,316
首先，这不是油画，这是素描
{\fscx80\fscy80}First of all, it's not a painting. It's a drawing.{\r}

1167
01:28:47,352 --> 01:28:49,650
只不过是用彩色蜡笔罢了
{\fscx80\fscy80}Matter of fact, it's a pastel and...{\r}

1168
01:28:49,721 --> 01:28:53,623
至于模特嘛 他只是非常气愤地向我走来
{\fscx80\fscy80}as for the model, just came to me out of the blue.{\r}

1169
01:28:53,725 --> 01:28:57,752
-你还没说呢 你那代理州长腔怎么怎么浓重啊？
{\fscx80\fscy80}- You don't say. - Why are you acting like a deputy sheriff?{\r}

1170
01:28:57,829 --> 01:29:00,593
我捉了个流浪汉 他偷了双鞋子
{\fscx80\fscy80}That tramp I picked up, the one with the stolen shoes?{\r}

1171
01:29:00,665 --> 01:29:03,395
他说是从死人那拿的
{\fscx80\fscy80}Said he got 'em off a dead man?{\r}

1172
01:29:03,468 --> 01:29:07,461
他非常细致地描述他一番 样子和你的画很相似
{\fscx80\fscy80}He described him very carefully. The description fits this picture to a "T. ''{\r}

1173
01:29:07,539 --> 01:29:11,475
那些流浪汉游手好闲 又喝得酩酊大醉….
{\fscx80\fscy80}A tramp who probably can't keep his job and drinks too much...{\r}

1174
01:29:11,543 --> 01:29:14,034
我认为他的话不大可信
{\fscx80\fscy80}I wouldn't think his word was very reliable.{\r}

1175
01:29:14,145 --> 01:29:17,444
他就被关在校舍里
{\fscx80\fscy80}Got him locked up in the schoolhouse.{\r}

1176
01:29:17,549 --> 01:29:20,017
-我拿这幅画给他看 请说素描，如果你不介意的话
{\fscx80\fscy80}I took this painting down to show him... Drawing, if you don't mind.{\r}

1177
01:29:20,084 --> 01:29:23,053
我拿这素描给他看 他几乎晕了过去
{\fscx80\fscy80}I took the drawing down to show him. He almost fainted.{\r}

1178
01:29:23,087 --> 01:29:26,215
说几乎是同一张脸 你在哪儿画的，山姆？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Said it was the same face. Where'd you paint it, Sam?{\r}

1179
01:29:28,493 --> 01:29:31,257
来自我的潜意识
{\fscx80\fscy80}From my vast subconscious.{\r}

1180
01:29:31,362 --> 01:29:35,264
山姆，我不想这样说 但我不能相信你的话
{\fscx80\fscy80}Sam, I hate to say this, but I don't believe you.{\r}

1181
01:29:35,300 --> 01:29:37,268
听这些让我打牌的兴趣 都丢光了
{\fscx80\fscy80}With all this talk, I've lost interest in the game.{\r}

1182
01:29:37,302 --> 01:29:39,862
请原谅，我得回家了
{\fscx80\fscy80}If you'll forgive me, I'll just run along home.{\r}

1183
01:29:39,971 --> 01:29:43,202
明天见吧
{\fscx80\fscy80}I'll see you all tOmOrrOw.{\r}

1184
01:29:45,176 --> 01:29:47,576
你说你不相信我是什么意思？
{\fscx80\fscy80}What do you mean, you don't believe me?{\r}

1185
01:29:47,612 --> 01:29:52,777
我的意思是，山姆 我可没接受过抽象美术的教育
{\fscx80\fscy80}What I mean, Sam... I ain't educated in fancy art,{\r}

1186
01:29:52,884 --> 01:29:56,684
但我看到这个后我就知道 死人的脸是怎样的啦，就是这样
{\fscx80\fscy80}but I do know the face of a dead man when I see one, and this is it.{\r}

1187
01:29:56,721 --> 01:30:00,589
加尔文，或许我可以教你 呃，“抽象艺术”
{\fscx80\fscy80}Calvin Perhaps I can teach you Abstract art{\r}

1188
01:30:01,726 --> 01:30:05,355
看到这个吧？ 是一张沉睡的脸的肖像
{\fscx80\fscy80}See this? Portrait of a sleeping face.{\r}

1189
01:30:05,430 --> 01:30:10,299
一个男人，非常的放松 远离尘嚣
{\fscx80\fscy80}A man, relaxed, far removed from earthly cares.{\r}

1190
01:30:10,335 --> 01:30:14,499
是由我的记忆还有一半的 激情而构思的
{\fscx80\fscy80}It was conceived out of memory and half-forgotten impulse,{\r}

1191
01:30:14,606 --> 01:30:17,074
它是抽象情绪的影子
{\fscx80\fscy80}and it emerged from the shadows of abstract emotions,{\r}

1192
01:30:17,141 --> 01:30:22,306
由我的指尖演变成现实
{\fscx80\fscy80}until it was born full-grown from the mechanical reality of my fingertips.{\r}

1193
01:30:22,413 --> 01:30:25,109
-噢，山姆，别….    -我
{\fscx80\fscy80}Oh, now Sam, don't... I don't have to have a model to draw from.{\r}

1194
01:30:25,216 --> 01:30:27,878
除了创作一张沉睡的脸 我还可以
{\fscx80\fscy80}Instead of creating a sleeping face, I could have, um,{\r}

1195
01:30:27,952 --> 01:30:31,285
选择一种完全不同的艺术表现
{\fscx80\fscy80}chosen an entirely different set of artistic stimuli.{\r}

1196
01:30:31,356 --> 01:30:35,588
我的下意识是很多张人脸 把地球覆盖了
{\fscx80\fscy80}My subconscious is peopled with enough faces to cover the earth.{\r}

1197
01:30:35,660 --> 01:30:40,120
而人类解剖构造又是可变的
{\fscx80\fscy80}And the construction of the human anatomy alone is so infinitely variable...{\r}

1198
01:30:40,164 --> 01:30:43,133
比人能思考的余力更大
{\fscx80\fscy80}as to lie beyond the wildest powers of calculation.{\r}

1199
01:30:43,234 --> 01:30:47,330
现在就变成了睁眼的了
{\fscx80\fscy80}Now, a raised eyelid, perhaps.{\r}

1200
01:30:50,441 --> 01:30:53,899
脸部也饱满多了
{\fscx80\fscy80}A line of fullness to the cheek.{\r}

1201
01:30:53,978 --> 01:30:56,674
连嘴唇也充满表情
{\fscx80\fscy80}Lip that bends with expression.{\r}

1202
01:30:58,550 --> 01:31:00,484
你看
{\fscx80\fscy80}There.{\r}

1203
01:31:01,753 --> 01:31:04,916
山姆，你知道你干了什么吗？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Sam, do you... Do you know what you just did?{\r}

1204
01:31:04,989 --> 01:31:09,187
当然 让你知道你曲解了我的艺术
{\fscx80\fscy80}Certainly. Just showed you how clearly you misinterpreted my art.{\r}

1205
01:31:09,260 --> 01:31:12,457
你破坏了法律证据
{\fscx80\fscy80}You just destroyed legal evidence.{\r}

1206
01:31:13,765 --> 01:31:17,599
加尔文，看来你还是不明白
{\fscx80\fscy80}Calvin, it appears to me you still don't understand.{\r}

1207
01:31:17,669 --> 01:31:20,661
我知道你在耍我
{\fscx80\fscy80}I understand you made kind of a fool out of me.{\r}

1208
01:31:20,705 --> 01:31:24,038
但我仍然还有足够的证据 去了解这里所发生的一切
{\fscx80\fscy80}But I still got enough evidence to know something funny's goin' on around here.{\r}

1209
01:31:24,108 --> 01:31:27,009
直到我找到真相前 我都不会去睡觉
{\fscx80\fscy80}I ain't goin' to sleep till I find out what it is.{\r}

1210
01:31:29,881 --> 01:31:32,475
晚安，加尔文
{\fscx80\fscy80}[Jennifer ] Good night, Calvin.{\r}

1211
01:31:36,321 --> 01:31:38,983
嘿！他在我们的浴缸干什么？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Hey! What's he doin' in our bathtub?{\r}

1212
01:31:42,026 --> 01:31:45,120
-那是青蛙的地方  -噢
{\fscx80\fscy80}- That's where frogs belong. - [ Arnie ] Oh.{\r}

1213
01:31:45,196 --> 01:31:48,962
-回去睡觉吧，安尼卡 -州际骑警早上会来的
{\fscx80\fscy80}- Back to bed, Arnie - State troopers'll be up in the mornin'.{\r}

1214
01:31:49,033 --> 01:31:52,298
我会让他们和他谈谈的啦
{\fscx80\fscy80}I'm gonna want 'em to have a talk with you, so be around.{\r}

1215
01:31:52,403 --> 01:31:55,395
-我说让你上床 -你可以在我工作室里找到我
{\fscx80\fscy80}- [Whispering] I said back to bed. - You can find me at my studio.{\r}

1216
01:31:55,506 --> 01:31:59,567
只是想确定
{\fscx80\fscy80}Just make sure... [Knocking At Door ]{\r}

1217
01:32:02,747 --> 01:32:04,715
他在哪儿？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Where is he?{\r}

1218
01:32:06,751 --> 01:32:08,912
他，他在浴室玩青蛙
{\fscx80\fscy80}He-He's in the bathroom playing with his frog.{\r}

1219
01:32:11,556 --> 01:32:15,515
-噢？ -我…这边有请 医生
{\fscx80\fscy80}- Oh? - I'm... This way, please, Doctor.{\r}

1220
01:32:17,328 --> 01:32:19,489
安尼卡.他不舒服
{\fscx80\fscy80}It's Arnie. He's not very well.{\r}

1221
01:32:23,167 --> 01:32:25,226
有人在搞我的车
{\fscx80\fscy80}Someone must be foolin' around with my car.{\r}

1222
01:32:36,481 --> 01:32:40,042
你在按什么喇叭？ 这可不是你的车啊
{\fscx80\fscy80}What are you playin' with the horn for? It ain't your car.{\r}

1223
01:32:40,151 --> 01:32:42,949
噢，只是觉得好玩
{\fscx80\fscy80}Well, things are funny, you know?{\r}

1224
01:32:43,054 --> 01:32:46,353
我和格勒夫利小姐 会去汽车市场买车
{\fscx80\fscy80}Me and Miss Gravely might be in the car market. We're looking for a car.{\r}

1225
01:32:46,457 --> 01:32:49,620
对，看看这辆，挺不错的
{\fscx80\fscy80}Yes. Had a look at this one. It's a beauty.{\r}

1226
01:32:49,694 --> 01:32:51,685
我就是要这样
{\fscx80\fscy80}I want to keep it that way.{\r}

1227
01:32:51,763 --> 01:32:55,028
噢，对潜在买家可不应该 用这种语气
{\fscx80\fscy80}Now, now, that's not the way to talk to a prospective customer.{\r}

1228
01:32:55,099 --> 01:32:58,432
你不是什么潜在买家 你买不起
{\fscx80\fscy80}You're no prospective customer. You can't afford this car.{\r}

1229
01:33:10,982 --> 01:33:12,882
他走了
{\fscx80\fscy80}He's gone.{\r}

1230
01:33:12,984 --> 01:33:16,613
我放这小…. 我安顿好安尼卡睡觉了
{\fscx80\fscy80}I put the little... I put Arnie back to bed.{\r}

1231
01:33:16,688 --> 01:33:19,589
医生说什么？他叫我出来
{\fscx80\fscy80}What'd the doctor say? He said for me to get out.{\r}

1232
01:33:19,691 --> 01:33:23,684
我不想看他的眼神 好像有什么让他遗憾似的
{\fscx80\fscy80}I didn't like the look in his eye, either. Something seems to be bothering him.{\r}

1233
01:33:26,230 --> 01:33:29,961
噢，船长.你怕完了吗？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Well, Captain. Did you get over being frightened?{\r}

1234
01:33:31,102 --> 01:33:33,627
害怕？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Frightened? [Laughing]{\r}

1235
01:33:33,705 --> 01:33:36,367
噢，不.这不是我要走的原因
{\fscx80\fscy80}Oh, no. That's not why I left.{\r}

1236
01:33:36,441 --> 01:33:39,968
不是，我可没那么容易害怕 你也清楚
{\fscx80\fscy80}No. I'm not easily frightened, you know. No.{\r}

1237
01:33:40,044 --> 01:33:44,003
噢，这些年来我周游了 世界的四个角
{\fscx80\fscy80}Why, after all those years sailing the four corners of the globe,{\r}

1238
01:33:44,048 --> 01:33:47,540
到过一些奇怪的港口 遇见过很多粗鲁的人
{\fscx80\fscy80}strange ports, a lot of rough men and...{\r}

1239
01:33:50,254 --> 01:33:54,350
格勒夫利小姐，你想说什么…
{\fscx80\fscy80}Miss Gravely, what would you say...{\r}

1240
01:33:54,425 --> 01:33:56,484
如果我告诉你…
{\fscx80\fscy80}if I told you...{\r}

1241
01:33:56,561 --> 01:33:59,553
我只是东江里的一艘拖船的
{\fscx80\fscy80}I was only the captain of a tugboat...{\r}

1242
01:33:59,630 --> 01:34:01,564
船长….
{\fscx80\fscy80}on the East River...{\r}

1243
01:34:01,632 --> 01:34:05,193
而且没跑过一公里或离开过岸 你会怎么想？
{\fscx80\fscy80}and never got more than a mile or so off shore?{\r}

1244
01:34:11,843 --> 01:34:14,505
噢，我会说
{\fscx80\fscy80}Well, I would say that,{\r}

1245
01:34:14,579 --> 01:34:17,343
你是一位英俊的从未 在东江上航行过的
{\fscx80\fscy80}that you were the handsomest tugboat captain...{\r}

1246
01:34:17,448 --> 01:34:19,643
拖船船长
{\fscx80\fscy80}that ever sailed up the East River.{\r}

1247
01:34:21,552 --> 01:34:24,146
噢，或许不是
{\fscx80\fscy80}[Chuckling] Oh, maybe not. No.{\r}

1248
01:34:24,255 --> 01:34:27,383
-你们想看点东西吗？ -这儿
{\fscx80\fscy80}You want to see something? Here.{\r}

1249
01:34:29,660 --> 01:34:31,560
-船长  -你在哪儿拿的？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Captain. Where'd you get those?{\r}

1250
01:34:31,662 --> 01:34:34,893
加尔文.维格斯的车里
{\fscx80\fscy80}Calvin Wiggs' car.{\r}

1251
01:34:34,966 --> 01:34:36,900
我想你们拿到了一半的证据 山姆
{\fscx80\fscy80}I figured you were handling half the evidence, Sammy,{\r}

1252
01:34:36,968 --> 01:34:39,163
那么其余的一半就由我来出马
{\fscx80\fscy80}so it was up to me to take care of the rest.{\r}

1253
01:34:39,270 --> 01:34:42,364
你是我吻过的最可爱的 老拖船船长
{\fscx80\fscy80}You're the sweetest, old tugboat captain I ever kissed.{\r}

1254
01:34:42,707 --> 01:34:45,403
他在浴室里干什么？
{\fscx80\fscy80}What's he doing in the bathtub?{\r}

1255
01:34:45,476 --> 01:34:48,274
噢，医生，你发现了什么？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Well, uh... What'd you find out, Doctor?{\r}

1256
01:34:48,379 --> 01:34:52,713
噢，他的心脏.他痉挛
{\fscx80\fscy80}Oh, that. It was his heart. He had a seizure.{\r}

1257
01:34:52,784 --> 01:34:55,514
-他的心脏？ -但
{\fscx80\fscy80}His heart? Yes, but...{\r}

1258
01:34:55,586 --> 01:34:58,680
-痉挛！ -我去过菲律宾群岛
{\fscx80\fscy80}A seizure! Well, I'll take a trip to the Philippines.{\r}

1259
01:34:58,790 --> 01:35:01,759
-自然死   -噢，当然
{\fscx80\fscy80}Death from natural causes. Well, certainly.{\r}

1260
01:35:01,826 --> 01:35:05,956
谁能告诉我他为什么 半裸着躺在浴缸里？
{\fscx80\fscy80}But will somebody tell me what he's doin' in the bathtub half undressed?{\r}

1261
01:35:07,899 --> 01:35:10,834
坦白地说，我们不想 让加尔文.维格斯看到他
{\fscx80\fscy80}Frankly, we didn't want Calvin Wiggs to see him.{\r}

1262
01:35:12,937 --> 01:35:15,428
而且，我们挖他起来时 他非常的脏
{\fscx80\fscy80}Besides, he was awful dirty after we dug him up.{\r}

1263
01:35:15,506 --> 01:35:17,906
“挖他起来？”
{\fscx80\fscy80}"Dug him up"?{\r}

1264
01:35:18,009 --> 01:35:20,705
我最好解释一下，医生
{\fscx80\fscy80}I'd better explain, Doctor. You see,{\r}

1265
01:35:20,812 --> 01:35:23,781
今天哈里又被埋 又被挖起有好几次了
{\fscx80\fscy80}Harry's been buried and dug up on and off all day long.{\r}

1266
01:35:23,848 --> 01:35:25,816
什么？
{\fscx80\fscy80}What?{\r}

1267
01:35:25,850 --> 01:35:28,114
他导致事情复杂化…
{\fscx80\fscy80}Finally, he caused so many complications that...{\r}

1268
01:35:28,219 --> 01:35:31,518
我们决定帮他冲洗一下 然后摆回原地
{\fscx80\fscy80}we decided to clean him up and put him back where we found him.{\r}

1269
01:35:31,622 --> 01:35:34,113
我不是很明白.什么复杂？
{\fscx80\fscy80}I don't understand you. What complications?{\r}

1270
01:35:34,225 --> 01:35:36,750
噢，举个例子
{\fscx80\fscy80}Well, for example,{\r}

1271
01:35:36,828 --> 01:35:40,229
他让船长大吃一惊 因为船长以为是他杀的
{\fscx80\fscy80}he upset Capt. Wiles because the captain thought he had shot him.{\r}

1272
01:35:40,331 --> 01:35:44,028
而他头上的伤口又表明 不是船长干的
{\fscx80\fscy80}The hole in the head, you know. But as it turned out, it wasn't the captain.{\r}

1273
01:35:44,135 --> 01:35:47,332
那是他骚扰格勒夫利小姐时 她用高跟鞋敲他的头
{\fscx80\fscy80}It was the blow he got from the heel of Miss Gravely's shoe after he attacked her.{\r}

1274
01:35:47,438 --> 01:35:50,134
怀尔斯船长骚扰格勒夫利小姐？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Capt. Wiles attacked Miss Gravely?{\r}

1275
01:35:50,241 --> 01:35:53,074
噢，不是.是哈里，医生
{\fscx80\fscy80}Oh, no, Doctor. Harry.{\r}

1276
01:35:53,144 --> 01:35:55,738
他把她拉进森林，以为是我
{\fscx80\fscy80}He dragged her into the bushes, thinking it was me.{\r}

1277
01:35:55,847 --> 01:36:00,045
我想他是有点晕头转向的 因为之前我用奶瓶敲了他的头
{\fscx80\fscy80}He was dazed, I supposed, after I hit him on the head with a milk bottle.{\r}

1278
01:36:04,088 --> 01:36:06,921
首先是船长和山姆埋他的
{\fscx80\fscy80}The captain and Sam buried him first.{\r}

1279
01:36:06,991 --> 01:36:09,653
船长很害怕
{\fscx80\fscy80}[Giggles] The captain was so scared.{\r}

1280
01:36:09,760 --> 01:36:14,163
接着他要数他的子弹 这样就把哈里挖出来了
{\fscx80\fscy80}Then he accounted for all his bullets, so up Harry came.{\r}

1281
01:36:14,198 --> 01:36:16,758
然后格勒夫利小姐是她的鞋子 把他打死的，所以…..
{\fscx80\fscy80}Then Miss Gravely thought her shoe was responsible for it so...{\r}

1282
01:36:16,868 --> 01:36:21,032
-鞋子？ -我觉得船长非常的勇敢….
{\fscx80\fscy80}- Shoe? - So the captain... rather gallantly, I thought...{\r}

1283
01:36:21,105 --> 01:36:23,073
又把他给埋了
{\fscx80\fscy80}pushed him back in again.{\r}

1284
01:36:23,107 --> 01:36:26,338
接着他又被挖出来又被埋下去 我都忘了原因
{\fscx80\fscy80}Then he was out and back... I can't remember why.{\r}

1285
01:36:26,410 --> 01:36:29,470
而现在他又被挖起来了 因为山姆和我要结婚了
{\fscx80\fscy80}But anyway, he's out again now because Sam and I wanna get married.{\r}

1286
01:36:29,580 --> 01:36:32,674
噢，但你为什么要….
{\fscx80\fscy80}Yeah. But why did you...{\r}

1287
01:36:32,783 --> 01:36:34,683
敲他的头？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Hit him on the head?{\r}

1288
01:36:34,785 --> 01:36:38,084
你不会对此感兴趣的 纯粹是个人而非医学问题
{\fscx80\fscy80}That wouldn't interest you. It's purely personal and nonmedical.{\r}

1289
01:36:38,189 --> 01:36:41,750
而且，现在也很晚了 如果你不对外说这事
{\fscx80\fscy80}Besides, it's awfully late, so if you'll just keep quiet about all this,{\r}

1290
01:36:41,826 --> 01:36:44,090
我们会在早上干净利落地 把哈里放回去
{\fscx80\fscy80}we'll put Harry back in the morning, nice and clean,{\r}

1291
01:36:44,195 --> 01:36:46,095
没什么人能明了
{\fscx80\fscy80}and no one will be any the wiser.{\r}

1292
01:36:46,197 --> 01:36:48,688
而且这样可以把复杂简单化
{\fscx80\fscy80}And then we'll be rid of all these sticky complications.{\r}

1293
01:36:48,799 --> 01:36:51,063
把他放回去，放回去 就这样.放回去
{\fscx80\fscy80}Put him back. Put him back, that's all. Just put him back.{\r}

1294
01:36:51,135 --> 01:36:54,434
这真是我25年来的头一个恶梦
{\fscx80\fscy80}This is the first nightmare I've had in 25 years.{\r}

1295
01:36:58,442 --> 01:37:00,307
他有点奇怪，是吧？
{\fscx80\fscy80}He's kinda strange, isn't he?{\r}

1296
01:37:06,617 --> 01:37:10,713
好了，我们该给他穿上衣服了
{\fscx80\fscy80}[Chuckling] Well, um, hadn't we better get Harry dressed?{\r}

1297
01:37:10,821 --> 01:37:12,755
对，对
{\fscx80\fscy80}[Sam] Yes, yes.{\r}

1298
01:37:19,363 --> 01:37:22,423
如果让安尼卡再找他一遍 会不会更好？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Wouldn't it be nice if Arnie found him all over again?{\r}

1299
01:37:22,533 --> 01:37:25,468
然后他可以跑回家告诉我 接着我就给加尔文.维格斯电话
{\fscx80\fscy80}Then he'd run home and tell me, and then I'd phone Calvin Wiggs.{\r}

1300
01:37:25,536 --> 01:37:28,699
对！安尼卡能对加尔文 解释清楚….
{\fscx80\fscy80}Yes! Arnie could explain quite clearly to Calvin...{\r}

1301
01:37:28,773 --> 01:37:32,675
-他在明天找哈里 -你是指今天吧
{\fscx80\fscy80}That he found Harry tomorrow. You mean today.{\r}

1302
01:37:32,743 --> 01:37:35,143
但对安尼卡来说 明天就是昨天
{\fscx80\fscy80}But to Arnie, tomorrow is yesterday.{\r}

1303
01:37:37,048 --> 01:37:39,039
我们去抬哈里.走，船长
{\fscx80\fscy80}Let's go get Harry. Come on, Captain.{\r}

1304
01:37:53,664 --> 01:37:55,564
他来了
{\fscx80\fscy80}Here he comes.{\r}

1305
01:38:15,219 --> 01:38:17,187
快，安尼卡.跑回家告诉我
{\fscx80\fscy80}Go on, Arnie. Run home and tell me about it.{\r}

1306
01:38:17,221 --> 01:38:19,189
别碰他
{\fscx80\fscy80}Don't touch him.{\r}

1307
01:38:19,223 --> 01:38:21,714
拜托了，安尼卡 跑回家告诉你的妈妈
{\fscx80\fscy80}Please, Arnie, run home and tell your mother.{\r}

1308
01:38:21,792 --> 01:38:23,885
打他，你这个讨厌鬼
{\fscx80\fscy80}Beat it, you little creep.{\r}

1309
01:38:23,995 --> 01:38:27,590
我是说，快回家吧，儿子
{\fscx80\fscy80}I mean, hurry home, son.{\r}

1310
01:38:36,741 --> 01:38:39,232
船长 你还没告诉过我你姓什么
{\fscx80\fscy80}Captain, you never told me your first name.{\r}

1311
01:38:39,310 --> 01:38:41,244
艾伯特.你呢？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Albert. What's yours?{\r}

1312
01:38:41,312 --> 01:38:45,510
艾维.艾伯特，我们走吧
{\fscx80\fscy80}Ivy. Albert, let's go.{\r}

1313
01:38:45,616 --> 01:38:47,516
等等，女士 我要问山姆一件事
{\fscx80\fscy80}Just a minute, ma'am. I want to ask Sam something.{\r}

1314
01:38:47,618 --> 01:38:50,553
山姆 你叫百万富翁带什么给你？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Sam, what did you ask the millionaire to bring you?{\r}

1315
01:38:59,063 --> 01:39:01,031
艾伯特，是什么？
{\fscx80\fscy80}Albert, what was it?{\r}

1316
01:39:02,333 --> 01:39:04,824
双人床
{\fscx80\fscy80}[Whispering] A double bed. [Laughing ]{\r}


